{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887524627,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b251ab0001N7OkPQQJVOmr9d","messageID":"msg_d7b250cba001PiikRNxPdaIsDB","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0bb01925ff224c21a704c8b2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: The purpose of this proposal is to create comprehensive architecture design documentation and API documentation for the AgentCube project. This documentation will:\n6: \n7: 1. Provide detailed architectural diagrams and component descriptions for the SDK and runtime system\n8: 2. Document all public APIs for the Python SDK, including client classes, services, and CLI commands\n9: 3. Establish a single source of truth for developers integrating with AgentCube\n10: 4. Enable faster onboarding for new team members and external developers\n11: 5. Support the existing Docusaurus documentation framework established in AR-042\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In scope\n16: \n17: | Item | Detail |\n18: |------|--------|\n19: | **Module path** | `docs` |\n20: | **Language** | Markdown (via Docusaurus) |\n21: | **Documentation type** | Architecture design + API reference |\n22: \n23: ### Architectural Documentation\n24: \n25: | Document | Description |\n26: |----------|-------------|\n27: | `docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md` | System-level architecture with component interactions |\n28: | `docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md` | SDK client architecture (AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient) |\n29: | `docs/docs/architecture/services.md` | Service layer architecture (MetadataService, DockerService, K8sProvider) |\n30: | `docs/docs/architecture/runtime.md` | Runtime operations architecture (Pack, Build, Publish, Invoke, Status) |\n31: | `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | Data flow diagrams and sequence diagrams |\n32: \n33: ### API Documentation\n34: \n35: | Document | Description |\n36: |----------|-------------|\n37: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md` | AgentRuntimeClient SDK API |\n38: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md` | CodeInterpreterClient SDK API |\n39: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md` | Service layer APIs |\n40: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md` | Runtime operation APIs |\n41: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md` | Exception reference |\n42: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md` | CLI command reference |\n43: \n44: ### Out of scope\n45: \n46: - Backend API documentation (Router, Control Plane, Data Plane endpoints)\n47: - Deployment and infrastructure documentation\n48: - User guides and tutorials (covered in existing docs)\n49: - Internal implementation details not exposed via public API\n50: \n51: ### Dependencies\n52: \n53: | Dependency | Usage |\n54: |------------|-------|\n55: | Docusaurus 3.x | Documentation framework (from AR-042) |\n56: | Existing `docs/docs/guides/architecture.md` | Current architecture content to be expanded |\n57: | Existing `docs/docs/api/*` | Current API docs to be replaced/enhanced |\n58: | Mermaid.js | Diagram rendering in Markdown |\n59: \n60: ## Design\n61: \n62: ### Directory structure additions\n63: \n64: ```\n65: docs/\n66: └── docs/\n67:     ├── architecture/           # New architecture docs\n68:     │   ├── system-design.md\n69:     │   ├── client-sdk.md\n70:     │   ├── services.md\n71:     │   ├── runtime.md\n72:     │   └── data-flow.md\n73:     └── api/\n74:         ├── sdk-agent-runtime.md\n75:         ├── sdk-code-interpreter.md\n76:         ├── sdk-services.md\n77:         ├── sdk-runtime.md\n78:         ├── sdk-exceptions.md\n79:         └── sdk-cli.md\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### Architecture documentation format\n83: \n84: ```markdown\n85: # Component Name\n86: \n87: ## Overview\n88: \n89: Brief description of the component's purpose and responsibilities.\n90: \n91: ## Architecture Diagram\n92: \n93: ```mermaid\n94: graph TB\n95:     A[Client] --> B[Router]\n96:     B --> C[Agent Runtime]\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ## Key Classes/Functions\n100: \n101: ### ClassName\n102: \n103: | Property/Method | Type | Description |\n104: |-----------------|------|-------------|\n105: | `param` | `str` | Description |\n106: \n107: ## Initialization\n108: \n109: ```python\n110: from agentcube import ClassName\n111: \n112: client = ClassName(param=\"value\")\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Use Cases\n116: \n117: 1. Use case 1\n118: 2. Use case 2\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### API documentation format\n122: \n123: ```markdown\n124: # SDK API Reference\n125: \n126: ## ClassName\n127: \n128: ### Constructor\n129: \n130: ```python\n131: ClassName(param1: str, param2: int = 10)\n132: ```\n133: \n134: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n135: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n136: | param1 | str | Required | Description |\n137: \n138: ### Methods\n139: \n140: #### method_name\n141: \n142: ```python\n143: client.method_name(arg1: str) -> dict\n144: ```\n145: \n146: **Parameters:**\n147: \n148: | Name | Type | Description |\n149: |------|------|-------------|\n150: | arg1 | str | Description |\n151: \n152: **Returns:** `dict` - Description\n153: \n154: **Raises:** `ExceptionType` - When condition\n155: \n156: **Example:**\n157: \n158: ```python\n159: result = client.method_name(\"value\")\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ## Exceptions\n163: \n164: | Exception | Description |\n165: |-----------|-------------|\n166: | `AgentCubeError` | Base exception |\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### Sidebar updates\n170: \n171: ```typescript\n172: // sidebars.ts addition\n173: {\n174:   type: 'category',\n175:   label: 'Architecture',\n176:   items: [\n177:     'architecture/system-design',\n178:     'architecture/client-sdk',\n179:     'architecture/services',\n180:     'architecture/runtime',\n181:     'architecture/data-flow',\n182:   ],\n183: },\n184: {\n185:   type: 'category',\n186:   label: 'SDK API Reference',\n187:   items: [\n188:     'api/sdk-agent-runtime',\n189:     'api/sdk-code-interpreter',\n190:     'api/sdk-services',\n191:     'api/sdk-runtime',\n192:     'api/sdk-exceptions',\n193:     'api/sdk-cli',\n194:   ],\n195: },\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ## Impact analysis\n199: \n200: ### Files created\n201: \n202: | File | Description |\n203: |------|-------------|\n204: | `docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md` | System architecture (~150 lines) |\n205: | `docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md` | SDK client architecture (~200 lines) |\n206: | `docs/docs/architecture/services.md` | Services architecture (~150 lines) |\n207: | `docs/docs/architecture/runtime.md` | Runtime operations (~150 lines) |\n208: | `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | Data flow diagrams (~100 lines) |\n209: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md` | AgentRuntimeClient API (~250 lines) |\n210: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md` | CodeInterpreterClient API (~300 lines) |\n211: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md` | Services API (~200 lines) |\n212: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md` | Runtime API (~200 lines) |\n213: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md` | Exceptions reference (~100 lines) |\n214: | `docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md` | CLI reference (~200 lines) |\n215: \n216: **Estimated total**: ~1800 lines\n217: \n218: ### Files modified\n219: \n220: | File | Change |\n221: |------|--------|\n222: | `docs/sidebars.ts` | Add architecture and SDK API categories |\n223: | `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | Add Mermaid support if needed |\n224: \n225: ### Dependencies\n226: \n227: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n228: |------------|---------|---------|\n229: | mermaid | ^10.0.0 | Diagram rendering |\n230: | @docusaurus/theme-mermaid | ^3.0.0 | Mermaid plugin for Docusaurus |\n231: \n232: ### Downstream consumers\n233: \n234: | Consumer | Dependency |\n235: |----------|-----------|\n236: | SDK users | Reference for integration |\n237: | Internal developers | Understanding architecture |\n238: | External contributors | Onboarding and contribution |\n239: | Technical writers | Maintain documentation |\n240: \n241: ### Breaking change risk\n242: \n243: **Very Low**: This is documentation-only work. No code changes are made. Existing documentation remains accessible alongside new content.\n244: \n245: ### Performance characteristics\n246: \n247: - **Build time impact**: Minimal (~5-10 seconds for new docs)\n248: - **Static site size**: ~1-2MB additional for diagrams\n249: - **Rendering**: Mermaid diagrams render client-side\n250: \n251: ### Edge cases handled\n252: \n253: 1. **Missing diagrams**: Graceful fallback with link to source\n254: 2. **Code examples**: Tested against actual SDK code\n255: 3. **API changes**: Documentation follows code conventions from source\n256: 4. **Cross-references**: Internal links between related docs\n257: \n258: ## Alternatives considered\n259: \n260: ### 1. Auto-generate from docstrings using pdoc/sphinx\n261: \n262: **Approach**: Use automated documentation generation from Python docstrings.\n263: \n264: **Rejected because**:\n265: - Generates API reference only, no architectural overview\n266: - Doesn't integrate with Docusaurus theme\n267: - Limited customization for different audiences\n268: - Requires additional tooling setup\n269: \n270: ### 2. Use OpenAPI/Swagger for API docs\n271: \n272: **Approach**: Define API contracts in OpenAPI spec and generate docs.\n273: \n274: **Rejected because**:\n275: - Primary API is Python SDK, not HTTP REST\n276: - CLI docs not covered by OpenAPI\n277: - Additional infrastructure needed for spec management\n278: - Less readable for SDK users\n279: \n280: ### 3. Use TypeDoc for JavaScript SDK documentation\n281: \n282: **Approach**: Use TypeDoc for generating JavaScript-focused API docs.\n283: \n284: **Rejected because**:\n285: - AgentCube SDK is Python-based\n286: - Doesn't integrate with existing Docusaurus\n287: - No support for architecture diagrams\n288: - Different audience from TypeScript developers\n289: \n290: ### 4. Use Sphinx with Read the Docs\n291: \n292: **Approach**: Use Sphinx (Python documentation tool) with Read the Docs.\n293: \n294: **Rejected because**:\n295: - Duplicates documentation framework (Docusaurus from AR-042)\n296: - Team expertise in Docusaurus/MDX\n297: - Less flexible theming\n298: - Multiple documentation sites\n299: \n300: ### 5. Focus only on REST API documentation\n301: \n302: **Approach**: Document only the HTTP API, not SDK.\n303: \n304: **Rejected because**:\n305: - Primary integration point is Python SDK\n306: - SDK provides better developer experience\n307: - CLI needs separate documentation\n308: - Incomplete coverage for users\n\n(End of file - total 308 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe purpose of this proposal is to create comprehensive architecture design documentation and API documentation for the AgentCube project. This documentation will:\n\n1. Provide detailed architectural diagrams and component descriptions for the SDK and runtime system\n2. Document all public APIs for the Python SDK, including client classes, services, and CLI commands\n3. Establish a single source of truth for developers integrating with AgentCube\n4. Enable faster onboarding for new team members and external developers\n5. Support the existing Docusaurus documentation framework established in AR-042\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `docs` |\n| **Language** | Markdown (via Docusaurus) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775887524601,"end":1775887524625}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887524631,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b251f85001jjY15SDqjXOxz3","messageID":"msg_d7b250cba001PiikRNxPdaIsDB","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a79b62b50a464d298aa310af","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing a Docusaurus documentation site framework for the AgentCube project.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-042\n10: - **Module**: `docs`\n11: - **Language**: TypeScript\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: AgentCube 需要一个现代化的文档站点来承载项目文档、API 参考、教程等内容。Docusaurus 是 Facebook 开发的开源静态网站生成器，专为技术文档设计，支持 Markdown、React 组件嵌入、版本管理和全文搜索等特性。\n19: \n20: docs 模块将作为独立的前端模块，位于项目根目录下的 `docs/` 目录，包含完整的 Docusaurus 配置和内容结构。\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## Requirements\n25: \n26: ### Feature: 项目初始化\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-042-001-A — 初始化 Docusaurus 项目\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** 一个空的 `docs/` 目录\n31: - **WHEN** 运行 `npx create-docusaurus@latest . classic` 命令\n32: - **THEN** Docusaurus 脚手架文件被生成\n33: - **AND** 包含 `docusaurus.config.js` 配置文件\n34: - **AND** 包含 `package.json` 依赖配置\n35: - **AND** 包含 `src/` 目录结构\n36: - **AND** 包含 `static/` 静态资源目录\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: AR-042-001-B — 安装依赖并验证\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** 生成的 Docusaurus 项目结构\n41: - **WHEN** 运行 `npm install` 安装依赖\n42: - **THEN** 所有 Docusaurus 核心依赖安装成功\n43: - **AND** 运行 `npm run build` 构建成功\n44: - **AND** 生成 `build/` 静态文件目录\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### Feature: 站点配置\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: AR-042-002-A — 配置站点基本信息\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 配置文件\n53: - **WHEN** 设置 `title` 为 \"AgentCube\"\n54: - **AND** 设置 `tagline` 为 \"Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents\"\n55: - **AND** 设置 `url` 为文档站点 URL\n56: - **AND** 设置 `baseUrl` 为 \"/\"\n57: - **THEN** 站点标题和副标题正确显示在首页\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-042-002-B — 配置导航栏\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 配置\n62: - **WHEN** 在 `themeConfig.navbar` 中配置导航栏\n63: - **AND** 添加 Logo 图片链接\n64: - **AND** 添加顶部菜单项：Docs、API、Blog、GitHub\n65: - **AND** 配置 GitHub 仓库链接\n66: - **THEN** 导航栏正确显示在页面顶部\n67: - **AND** 菜单项可点击跳转\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: AR-042-002-C — 配置页脚\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 配置\n72: - **WHEN** 在 `themeConfig.footer` 中配置页脚\n73: - **AND** 添加版权信息\n74: - **AND** 添加社交链接\n75: - **THEN** 页脚正确显示在页面底部\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: AR-042-002-D — 配置 Prism 代码高亮\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 配置\n80: - **WHEN** 在 `themeConfig.prism` 中配置代码高亮\n81: - **AND** 添加支持的语言：javascript, typescript, python, go, yaml, bash, json, markdown\n82: - **THEN** 代码块正确高亮显示\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ### Feature: 文档结构\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: AR-042-003-A — 创建文档侧边栏\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** `docs/` 目录下有多个 MDX 文件\n91: - **WHEN** 配置文件侧边栏 `sidebars.js`\n92: - **AND** 定义分类：Getting Started、Architecture、API Reference、Tutorials\n93: - **THEN** 侧边栏正确显示在文档页面左侧\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: AR-042-003-B — 文档元数据配置\n96: \n97: - **GIVEN** 一个 MDX 文档文件\n98: - **WHEN** 在文件头部添加元数据\n99: - **AND** 设置 `id`、`title`、`sidebar_position`\n100: - **THEN** 文档正确渲染，元数据生效\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: AR-042-003-C — 创建版本文档\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** 已有文档内容\n105: - **WHEN** 运行 `npm run docusaurus docs:version 1.0.0`\n106: - **THEN** 生成 `versioned_docs/version-1.0.0/` 目录\n107: - **AND** 生成 `versioned_sidebars/version-1.0.0-sidebars.json`\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ### Feature: 搜索功能\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: AR-042-004-A — 配置本地搜索\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n116: - **WHEN** 安装 `@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local` 插件\n117: - **AND** 在配置中启用插件\n118: - **THEN** 搜索框出现在页面顶部\n119: - **AND** 搜索功能可正常使用\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ### Feature: 国际化 (i18n)\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: AR-042-005-A — 配置多语言支持\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 配置\n128: - **WHEN** 在 `i18n` 中配置默认语言为英语\n129: - **AND** 添加中文语言支持\n130: - **THEN** 语言切换器出现在导航栏\n131: - **AND** 切换语言后界面显示对应语言\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Feature: 部署配置\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AR-042-006-A — 配置 GitHub Pages 部署\n138: \n139: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n140: - **WHEN** 在 `package.json` 中配置 deploy 命令\n141: - **AND** 配置 GitHub Actions 工作流\n142: - **THEN** 代码推送后自动部署到 GitHub Pages\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: AR-042-006-B — 构建生产版本\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n147: - **WHEN** 运行 `npm run build`\n148: - **THEN** 生成优化的静态文件\n149: - **AND** HTML 文件包含正确的 baseUrl 路径\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### Feature: 自定义组件\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: AR-042-007-A — 添加自定义 CSS 主题\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n158: - **WHEN** 在 `src/css/custom.css` 中添加自定义样式\n159: - **THEN** 自定义样式正确应用到站点\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: AR-042-007-B — 创建自定义 React 组件\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n164: - **WHEN** 在 `src/components/` 中创建 React 组件\n165: - **AND** 在 MDX 文件中导入使用\n166: - **THEN** 组件正确渲染\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ### Feature: 开发服务器\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AR-042-008-A — 启动开发服务器\n173: \n174: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n175: - **WHEN** 运行 `npm start`\n176: - **THEN** 开发服务器启动在 localhost:3000\n177: - **AND** 热更新功能正常工作\n178: - **AND** 文件修改后页面自动刷新\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: AR-042-008-B — 类型检查\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** Docusaurus 项目\n183: - **WHEN** 运行 TypeScript 类型检查\n184: - **THEN** 无类型错误\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ### Feature: 文档内容示例\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: AR-042-009-A — 创建入门文档\n191: \n192: - **GIVEN** 需要创建入门指南\n193: - **WHEN** 创建 `docs/getting-started/installation.mdx`\n194: - **AND** 包含安装步骤、配置说明\n195: - **THEN** 文档正确渲染在侧边栏中\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-042-009-B — 创建 API 文档\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** 需要创建 API 参考文档\n200: - **WHEN** 创建 `docs/api-reference/overview.mdx`\n201: - **AND** 包含 API 端点说明、请求/响应示例\n202: - **THEN** API 文档正确显示代码示例\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Acceptance Criteria\n207: \n208: - [ ] AC001: Docusaurus 项目初始化成功，依赖安装完成\n209: - [ ] AC002: 站点配置（标题、导航栏、页脚、代码高亮）正确\n210: - [ ] AC003: 文档侧边栏结构正确，文档元数据生效\n211: - [ ] AC004: 搜索功能正常工作\n212: - [ ] AC005: 国际化配置正确，语言切换功能可用\n213: - [ ] AC006: GitHub Pages 部署配置正确\n214: - [ ] AC007: 自定义 CSS 和 React 组件可正常使用\n215: - [ ] AC008: 开发服务器正常运行，热更新有效\n216: - [ ] AC009: 构建生产版本成功，静态文件生成\n217: - [ ] AC010: 包含至少 5 篇文档：Installation、Quick Start、Architecture、API Reference、Troubleshooting\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Architecture Notes\n222: \n223: ### 目录结构\n224: \n225: ```\n226: docs/\n227: ├── docusaurus.config.js      # Docusaurus 主配置\n228: ├── sidebars.js                # 侧边栏配置\n229: ├── package.json               # 依赖配置\n230: ├── src/\n231: │   ├── css/\n232: │   │   └── custom.css        # 自定义样式\n233: │   ├── pages/\n234: │   │   ├── index.tsx         # 首页\n235: │   │   └── ...                # 其他页面\n236: ├── static/\n237: │   └── img/                   # 静态图片\n238: └── docs/                      # 文档目录\n239:     ├── getting-started/\n240:     ├── architecture/\n241:     ├── api-reference/\n242:     └── tutorials/\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ### 关键配置项\n246: \n247: | 配置项 | 说明 | 示例值 |\n248: |--------|------|--------|\n249: | title | 站点标题 | \"AgentCube\" |\n250: | tagline | 站点副标题 | \"Kubernetes-native sandbox...\" |\n251: | url | 站点 URL | \"https://agentcube.ai\" |\n252: | baseUrl | 基础路径 | \"/\" |\n253: | prism.additionalLanguages | 代码高亮语言 | [\"go\", \"python\", \"yaml\"] |\n254: \n255: ### 依赖包\n256: \n257: ```json\n258: {\n259:   \"dependencies\": {\n260:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.0.0\",\n261:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.0.0\",\n262:     \"@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local\": \"^0.44.0\",\n263:     \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n264:     \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n265:   }\n266: }\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## References\n272: \n273: - Docusaurus 官方文档: https://docusaurus.io/\n274: - Docusaurus 配置参考: https://docusaurus.io/docs/configuration\n275: - Docusaurus i18n: https://docusaurus.io/docs/i18n\n276: - GitHub Pages 部署: https://docusaurus.io/docs/deployment\n\n(End of file - total 276 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing a Docusaurus documentation site framework for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-042\n- **Module**: `docs`\n- **Language**: TypeScript\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube 需要一个现代化的文档站点来承载项目文档、API 参考、教程等内容。Docusaurus 是 Facebook 开发的开源静态网站生成器，专为技术文档设计，支持 Markdown、React 组件嵌入、版本管理和全文搜索等特性。\n\ndocs 模块将作为独立的前端模块，位于项目根目录下的 `docs/` 目录，包含完整的 Docusaurus 配置和内容结构。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887524605,"end":1775887524628}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775887524660,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b252316001VoQKttt9R8EeKw","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b250cba001PiikRNxPdaIsDB","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20166,"input":4978,"output":162,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15026}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887528157,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2530d9001SMgFOo4pcJGt82","messageID":"msg_d7b25234c001ovRzg5Alv827be","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887532160,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2533860010Lkh7GxA9sGYoB","messageID":"msg_d7b25234c001ovRzg5Alv827be","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_50cd973e64de4431ac316621","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775887532143,"end":1775887532158}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887532162,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b253c2c001nBgLHzZC2j7AYP","messageID":"msg_d7b25234c001ovRzg5Alv827be","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9e55916204694cf38fd3f1f3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-routing/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-routing/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Route HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\n9: The system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n12: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n13: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n14: - **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n17: - **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n18: - **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n19: - **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Workload manager URL and auth token for creates\n22: The system SHALL require environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` at session manager construction (non-empty). When the file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists and is readable, the system SHALL attach `Authorization: Bearer <trimmed contents>` to create requests.\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Missing WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL fails startup\n25: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is unset\n26: - **WHEN** `NewSessionManager` is called\n27: - **THEN** it returns error `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is not set`\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Create response validation\n30: The system SHALL accept workload manager HTTP 200 with body `CreateSandboxResponse`; SHALL reject with internal error if `sessionId` in body is empty; SHALL build in-memory `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID`, `Name` (= `sandboxName`), `SessionID`, `EntryPoints` from the response (other fields may be zero).\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Non-OK from workload manager\n33: - **GIVEN** workload manager returns HTTP 404\n34: - **WHEN** the session manager handles the response\n35: - **THEN** the error is `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind)`\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy to sandbox\n38: The system SHALL determine upstream URL from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` by first matching `path` prefix against the invocation path; if none match, SHALL use the first entry point. The system SHALL build URL by prefixing `protocol` (lowercase) and `://` to `endpoint` when protocol is set and endpoint lacks a scheme. The system SHALL use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`, shared `http.Transport` on the proxy, and custom `Director` to set path, host, forwarding headers, and optional JWT.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: No entry points\n41: - **GIVEN** `EntryPoints` is empty\n42: - **WHEN** upstream is determined\n43: - **THEN** the handler responds 404 JSON `{\"error\":\"no entry point found for sandbox\"}`\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: JWT injection for sandbox kinds\n46: For sandbox kinds `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim`, the system SHALL generate a JWT before proxying and SHALL set `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on the proxied request.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Signing failure\n49: - **GIVEN** JWT generation returns an error\n50: - **WHEN** forwarding is attempted\n51: - **THEN** the handler responds 500 with JSON containing `\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"` and `\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Forwarding headers and response header\n54: The system SHALL set `X-Forwarded-Host` from the incoming request host, `X-Forwarded-Proto` to `https` when TLS is present else `http`, and `X-Forwarded-For` by appending client IP to any existing values. The system SHALL set response header `x-agentcube-session-id` to the resolved session id on all proxied responses.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Path normalization\n57: - **GIVEN** the Gin path param is non-empty and lacks a leading slash\n58: - **WHEN** the director runs\n59: - **THEN** the outbound path is prefixed with `/`\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Proxy error mapping\n62: The system SHALL map proxy errors containing `connection refused` to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`, containing `timeout` to 504 `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}`, and other errors to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Downstream connection refused\n65: - **GIVEN** the reverse proxy fails with an error whose message includes `connection refused`\n66: - **WHEN** `ErrorHandler` runs\n67: - **THEN** status is 502 and error text is `sandbox unreachable`\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Last-activity updates\n70: The system SHALL call `UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()` after successfully resolving the sandbox and again after `forwardToSandbox` returns (twice per successful invoke path). Failures SHALL be logged as warnings only.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Store update failure does not block proxy\n73: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` returns an error\n74: - **WHEN** handling continues\n75: - **THEN** the proxy still runs if sandbox resolution succeeded\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Health endpoints\n78: The system SHALL expose `GET /health/live` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`. The system SHALL expose `GET /health/ready` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` when session manager is non-nil, else 503 with `status` and `error` fields.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Ready depends on session manager\n81: - **GIVEN** `sessionManager` is nil\n82: - **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is served\n83: - **THEN** status is 503 and body includes `\"error\":\"session manager not available\"`\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Concurrency limiting\n86: The system SHALL apply a semaphore middleware to `/v1/*` routes with capacity `MaxConcurrentRequests` (default 1000 when config value ≤ 0). When no slot is available, the system SHALL respond 429 JSON `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` and abort.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default limit when zero in config\n89: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` receives `MaxConcurrentRequests` 0\n90: - **WHEN** the server is constructed\n91: - **THEN** the effective limit is set to 1000 before route registration\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Invocation route surface\n94: The system SHALL register GET and POST for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` and for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`, with Gin logger, recovery, and concurrency middleware on the `/v1` group only.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Kind passed to session lookup\n97: - **GIVEN** agent-runtime invocation\n98: - **WHEN** `handleInvoke` runs\n99: - **THEN** kind argument is `AgentRuntime` (`types.AgentRuntimeKind`)\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: HTTP server behavior\n102: The system SHALL serve with `h2c` and `http2.Server`, `ReadTimeout` 30s, `IdleTimeout` 90s; on context cancel SHALL shutdown within 10s. Optional TLS SHALL require both cert and key paths.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: TLS misconfiguration\n105: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` true and empty cert path\n106: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n107: - **THEN** it returns error stating cert/key not provided\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Identity secret bootstrap for JWT\n110: On server creation the system SHALL construct `JWTManager`, call `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`, and fail server creation if that returns error (except in-cluster skip path returns nil when not in cluster).\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: In-cluster secret creation\n113: - **GIVEN** in-cluster config succeeds and secret does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` runs\n115: - **THEN** it creates opaque secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` or `default` with keys `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRoute HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\nThe system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n- **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n- **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n- **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-routing/spec.md","time":{"start":1775887532149,"end":1775887532160}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887532164,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2537cb001sUR1NkMiriI1e7","messageID":"msg_d7b25234c001ovRzg5Alv827be","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_974fbfc38c434cfab7c0f6fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775887532147,"end":1775887532163}}}}
