{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887548052,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b25772f001VoY8mAfYLdQmZt","messageID":"msg_d7b256de20012C23MrH75mudB9","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_03d6e29c449a4884a87b0c01","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/guides/architecture.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/guides/architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: architecture\n3: title: Architecture Overview\n4: description: Understanding the AgentCube architecture\n5: sidebar_position: 1\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Architecture Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube is built with a microservices architecture designed for scalability, reliability, and maintainability. This document provides an in-depth look at each component.\n11: \n12: ## High-Level Architecture\n13: \n14: ```mermaid\n15: graph TB\n16:     subgraph Clients\n17:         A[Web App]\n18:         B[Mobile App]\n19:         C[API Client]\n20:     end\n21:     \n22:     subgraph Gateway\n23:         D[Load Balancer]\n24:     end\n25:     \n26:     subgraph Core\n27:         E[Router]\n28:         F[Agent Runtime]\n29:         G[Code Interpreter]\n30:     end\n31:     \n32:     subgraph Storage\n33:         H[(PostgreSQL)]\n34:         I[(Redis)]\n35:         J[S3]\n36:     end\n37:     \n38:     subgraph Management\n39:         K[Workload Manager]\n40:         L[Session Routing]\n41:     end\n42:     \n43:     A --> D\n44:     B --> D\n45:     C --> D\n46:     D --> E\n47:     E --> F\n48:     F --> G\n49:     F --> H\n50:     F --> I\n51:     G --> I\n52:     K --> F\n53:     L --> E\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ## Core Components\n57: \n58: ### Router\n59: \n60: The Router is the entry point for all requests. It handles:\n61: \n62: - **Request routing**: Directs requests to appropriate agent runtimes\n63: - **Load balancing**: Distributes load across multiple instances\n64: - **Rate limiting**: Prevents abuse and ensures fair usage\n65: - **Authentication**: Validates API keys and tokens\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: // Router configuration\n69: type RouterConfig struct {\n70:     Port         int\n71:     MaxConns     int\n72:     Timeout      time.Duration\n73:     RateLimit    RateLimitConfig\n74:     TLS          TLSConfig\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Agent Runtime\n79: \n80: The Agent Runtime is the core execution environment for AI agents. It manages:\n81: \n82: - **Agent lifecycle**: Creation, execution, and termination\n83: - **Session management**: Maintains state across interactions\n84: - **Tool execution**: Runs agent tools (code interpreter, etc.)\n85: - **Error handling**: Implements retry logic and fallback strategies\n86: \n87: ```go\n88: type AgentRuntime struct {\n89:     ID           string\n90:     Name         string\n91:     Model        string\n92:     Instructions string\n93:     Tools        []Tool\n94:     State        AgentState\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Code Interpreter\n99: \n100: The Code Interpreter provides secure code execution capabilities:\n101: \n102: - **Sandboxed execution**: Code runs in isolated containers\n103: - **Multiple languages**: Python, JavaScript, Go support\n104: - **Resource limits**: CPU, memory, and time constraints\n105: - **Output capture**: Stdout, stderr, and file outputs\n106: \n107: ### Session Store\n108: \n109: The Session Store handles persistent session data:\n110: \n111: - **PostgreSQL**: Primary data store for sessions and metadata\n112: - **Redis**: Caching layer for fast access\n113: - **Automatic cleanup**: Removes idle sessions\n114: \n115: ### Session Routing\n116: \n117: The Session Routing component ensures session affinity:\n118: \n119: - **Sticky sessions**: Routes requests to the same runtime\n120: - **Load distribution**: Balances across runtimes\n121: - **Failover**: Handles runtime failures gracefully\n122: \n123: ### Workload Manager\n124: \n125: The Workload Manager orchestrates agent workloads:\n126: \n127: - **Scaling**: Adds/removes runtime instances\n128: - **Placement**: Optimizes resource allocation\n129: - **Monitoring**: Tracks performance metrics\n130: \n131: ## Data Flow\n132: \n133: 1. **Request received** → Router validates and authenticates\n134: 2. **Routing** → Session Routing determines target runtime\n135: 3. **Execution** → Agent Runtime processes the request\n136: 4. **Tool call** → Code Interpreter executes code if needed\n137: 5. **Response** → Results returned to client\n138: 6. **State saved** → Session state persisted\n139: \n140: ## Scaling\n141: \n142: AgentCube supports horizontal scaling at each layer:\n143: \n144: - **Router**: Multiple instances behind load balancer\n145: - **Runtime**: Auto-scaling based on load\n146: - **Storage**: PostgreSQL read replicas\n147: - **Cache**: Redis cluster mode\n148: \n149: ## Security\n150: \n151: Security features include:\n152: \n153: - **TLS encryption**: All communications encrypted\n154: - **API keys**: Per-agent authentication\n155: - **Sandboxing**: Isolated execution environments\n156: - **Audit logging**: All actions logged\n157: \n158: ## Monitoring\n159: \n160: Each component exposes metrics:\n161: \n162: - **Request rate**: Requests per second\n163: - **Latency**: P50, P95, P99 response times\n164: - **Error rate**: Failed requests percentage\n165: - **Resource usage**: CPU, memory, network\n166: \n167: ## Next Steps\n168: \n169: - [Configuration Guide](/docs/guides/configuration)\n170: - [Monitoring Guide](/docs/guides/monitoring)\n171: - [API Reference](/docs/api/agent-runtime)\n\n(End of file - total 171 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: architecture\ntitle: Architecture Overview\ndescription: Understanding the AgentCube architecture\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# Architecture Overview\n\nAgentCube is built with a microservices architecture designed for scalability, reliability, and maintainability. This document provides an in-depth look at each component.\n\n## High-Level Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph Clients\n        A[Web App]\n        B[Mobile App]\n        C[API Client]\n    end","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/guides/architecture.md","time":{"start":1775887548037,"end":1775887548050}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887548054,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b257ae0001L6Prvm94S1BH5C","messageID":"msg_d7b256de20012C23MrH75mudB9","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7fb4edf953444ff2b8ea95c8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: agent-runtime\n3: title: Agent Runtime API\n4: description: Agent Runtime API reference\n5: sidebar_position: 1\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Agent Runtime API\n9: \n10: The Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n11: \n12: ## Base URL\n13: \n14: ```\n15: http://localhost:8080/api/v1\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: All API requests require an API key in the header:\n21: \n22: ```bash\n23: curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" ...\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ## Endpoints\n27: \n28: ### Create Agent\n29: \n30: Create a new agent.\n31: \n32: ```http\n33: POST /agents\n34: ```\n35: \n36: **Request Body:**\n37: \n38: ```json\n39: {\n40:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n41:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n42:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n43:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n44:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\", \"web-search\"],\n45:   \"metadata\": {\n46:     \"team\": \"engineering\"\n47:   }\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: **Response:**\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n56:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n57:   \"status\": \"active\",\n58:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Get Agent\n63: \n64: Retrieve agent details.\n65: \n66: ```http\n67: GET /agents/{agent_id}\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **Response:**\n71: \n72: ```json\n73: {\n74:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n75:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n76:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n77:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n78:   \"status\": \"active\",\n79:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n80:   \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n81: }\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### List Agents\n85: \n86: List all agents.\n87: \n88: ```http\n89: GET /agents\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **Query Parameters:**\n93: \n94: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n95: |-----------|------|-------------|\n96: | `limit` | int | Max results (default: 20) |\n97: | `offset` | int | Pagination offset |\n98: | `status` | string | Filter by status |\n99: \n100: **Response:**\n101: \n102: ```json\n103: {\n104:   \"agents\": [\n105:     {\n106:       \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n107:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n108:       \"status\": \"active\"\n109:     }\n110:   ],\n111:   \"total\": 1\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Update Agent\n116: \n117: Update an existing agent.\n118: \n119: ```http\n120: PATCH /agents/{agent_id}\n121: ```\n122: \n123: **Request Body:**\n124: \n125: ```json\n126: {\n127:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful coding assistant.\",\n128:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\"]\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Delete Agent\n133: \n134: Delete an agent.\n135: \n136: ```http\n137: DELETE /agents/{agent_id}\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Response:** `204 No Content`\n141: \n142: ### Invoke Agent\n143: \n144: Invoke an agent to process a request.\n145: \n146: ```http\n147: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Request Body:**\n151: \n152: ```json\n153: {\n154:   \"message\": \"Hello, how are you?\",\n155:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n156:   \"stream\": false,\n157:   \"context\": {}\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Response:**\n162: \n163: ```json\n164: {\n165:   \"response\": \"I'm doing well, thank you!\",\n166:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n167:   \"usage\": {\n168:     \"input_tokens\": 10,\n169:     \"output_tokens\": 15,\n170:     \"total_tokens\": 25\n171:   }\n172: }\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ### Stream Invoke\n176: \n177: Invoke an agent with streaming response.\n178: \n179: ```http\n180: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Request Body:**\n184: \n185: ```json\n186: {\n187:   \"message\": \"Write a story\",\n188:   \"stream\": true\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: **Response (Server-Sent Events):**\n193: \n194: ```stream\n195: data: {\"chunk\": \"Once\", \"done\": false}\n196: data: {\"chunk\": \" upon\", \"done\": false}\n197: data: {\"chunk\": \" a time\", \"done\": false}\n198: data: {\"done\": true}\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Types\n202: \n203: ### Agent\n204: \n205: ```typescript\n206: interface Agent {\n207:   id: string;\n208:   name: string;\n209:   description?: string;\n210:   model: string;\n211:   instructions: string;\n212:   tools: string[];\n213:   metadata: Record<string, string>;\n214:   status: 'active' | 'paused' | 'deleted';\n215:   created_at: string;\n216:   updated_at: string;\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### InvocationRequest\n221: \n222: ```typescript\n223: interface InvocationRequest {\n224:   message: string;\n225:   session_id?: string;\n226:   stream?: boolean;\n227:   context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n228:   temperature?: number;\n229:   max_tokens?: number;\n230: }\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### InvocationResponse\n234: \n235: ```typescript\n236: interface InvocationResponse {\n237:   response: string;\n238:   session_id: string;\n239:   usage: {\n240:     input_tokens: number;\n241:     output_tokens: number;\n242:     total_tokens: number;\n243:   };\n244:   metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;\n245: }\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## Error Codes\n249: \n250: | Code | Description |\n251: |------|-------------|\n252: | `400` | Bad Request |\n253: | `401` | Unauthorized |\n254: | `404` | Agent Not Found |\n255: | `429` | Rate Limited |\n256: | `500` | Internal Server Error |\n257: | `503` | Service Unavailable |\n258: \n259: ## Rate Limits\n260: \n261: - **Standard**: 60 requests/minute\n262: - **Pro**: 600 requests/minute\n263: - **Enterprise**: Custom\n264: \n265: ## SDK Examples\n266: \n267: ### Python\n268: \n269: ```python\n270: from agentcube import AgentRuntime\n271: \n272: client = AgentRuntime(api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\n273: \n274: response = client.invoke(\n275:     agent_id=\"agent_abc123\",\n276:     message=\"Hello!\"\n277: )\n278: print(response.response)\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### JavaScript\n282: \n283: ```javascript\n284: import { AgentRuntime } from '@agentcube/sdk';\n285: \n286: const client = new AgentRuntime({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });\n287: \n288: const response = await client.invoke({\n289:   agentId: 'agent_abc123',\n290:   message: 'Hello!'\n291: });\n292: \n293: console.log(response.response);\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ## Next Steps\n297: \n298: - [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/code-interpreter)\n299: - [CLI Reference](/docs/api/cli)\n\n(End of file - total 299 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: agent-runtime\ntitle: Agent Runtime API\ndescription: Agent Runtime API reference\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# Agent Runtime API\n\nThe Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:8080/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API requests require an API key in the header:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md","time":{"start":1775887548040,"end":1775887548052}}}}
