{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887622513,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b264324001bS91K62Jp7Bsde","messageID":"msg_d7b263946001sJ6TLSHhH2tbTm","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f2e049100bd34099845a3fb2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: system-design\ntitle: System Design\ndescription: AgentCube system-level architecture and component interactions\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# System Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform designed for AI agents. The system provides secure, isolated execution environments for agent runtimes and code interpreters, enabling dynamic workload management and session-based routing.\n\n## High-Level Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph \"External Clients\"\n        CLI[CLI Tool]\n        SDK[Python SDK]\n        External[External API]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"AgentCube Gateway\"\n        Router[Router Service]\n        LB[Load Balancer]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Control Plane\"\n        WM[Workload Manager]\n        CP[Control Plane Client]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Data Plane\"\n        DP[Data Plane Client]\n        SessionStore[(Session Store<br/>Redis)]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Execution Runtime\"\n        AR[Agent Runtime]\n        CI[Code Interpreter]\n        Pods[Sandbox Pods]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Kubernetes\"\n        K8s[Kubernetes Cluster]\n        CRD[AgentRuntime CRD]\n    end\n    \n    CLI --> Router\n    SDK --> Router\n    External --> LB\n    LB --> Router\n    Router --> WM\n    Router --> SessionStore\n    Router --> AR\n    Router --> CI\n    WM --> K8s\n    K8s --> Pods\n    K8s --> CRD\n    AR --> Pods\n    CI --> Pods\n```\n\n## Core Components\n\n### Router Service\n\nThe Router is the primary entry point for all client requests. It handles:\n\n- **Session Management**: Creates and tracks session IDs for agent invocations\n- **Request Routing**: Routes requests to appropriate agent runtimes based on namespace and name\n- **Reverse Proxy**: Forwards requests to sandbox pods with proper header forwarding\n- **JWT Injection**: Signs outbound requests with JWT for sandbox authentication\n- **Load Balancing**: Distributes requests across available sandbox instances\n\n**Technology**: Go with Gin web framework\n\n**Key Features**:\n- H2C and HTTP/2 support\n- Configurable timeouts (ReadTimeout: 30s, IdleTimeout: 90s)\n- Optional TLS support\n- Semaphore-based concurrency limiting (default: 1000 concurrent requests)\n\n### Workload Manager\n\nThe Workload Manager orchestrates agent lifecycle:\n\n- **Agent Deployment**: Creates AgentRuntime custom resources in Kubernetes\n- **Scaling Management**: Handles replica count and resource allocation\n- **Health Monitoring**: Tracks agent health and readiness\n- **Session Coordination**: Works with the Router for session affinity\n\n**Technology**: Go with controller-runtime\n\n### Session Store\n\nThe Session Store maintains session state:\n\n- **Redis Backend**: Primary session storage with TTL support\n- **Session Tracking**: Tracks last activity timestamps for idle detection\n- **Sandbox Information**: Stores endpoint and routing information\n\n### Code Interpreter\n\nThe Code Interpreter provides isolated code execution:\n\n- **Containerized Execution**: Runs code in isolated Kubernetes pods\n- **Multi-language Support**: Python, JavaScript, and shell commands\n- **File Operations**: Support for file upload, download, and listing\n- **Resource Limits**: CPU, memory, and execution time constraints\n\n## Data Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client\n    participant Router\n    participant SessionStore\n    participant WorkloadManager\n    participant K8s\n    participant Sandbox\n\n    Client->>Router: Invoke (no session)\n    Router->>WorkloadManager: Create Sandbox\n    WorkloadManager->>K8s: Create AgentRuntime CR\n    K8s->>Sandbox: Provision Pod\n    Sandbox-->>WorkloadManager: Ready\n    WorkloadManager-->>Router: Sandbox Info\n    Router->>SessionStore: Store Session\n    Router->>Client: Session ID + Response\n\n    Client->>Router: Invoke (with session)\n    Router->>SessionStore: Get Session\n    SessionStore-->>Router: Sandbox Info\n    Router->>Sandbox: Proxy Request\n    Sandbox-->>Router: Response\n    Router->>SessionStore: Update Last Activity\n    Router->>Client: Response\n```\n\n## Network Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"Public Network\"\n        User[User/Client]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Kubernetes Cluster\"\n        subgraph \"agentcube Namespace\"\n            Router[Router Service<br/>agentcube-router]\n            WM[Workload Manager<br/>workloadmanager]\n            Redis[(Redis)]\n        end\n        \n        subgraph \"User Namespace\"\n            AR[Agent Runtime Pod]\n            CI[Code Interpreter Pod]\n        end\n    end\n    \n    User --\"HTTPS\"--> Router\n    Router --\"HTTP/JWT\"--> AR\n    Router --\"HTTP/JWT\"--> CI\n    Router --\"HTTP\"--> WM\n    Router --\"Redis\"--> Redis\n    WM --\"K8s API\"--> AR\n    WM --\"K8s API\"--> CI\n```\n\n## Security Model\n\n### Authentication\n\n- **ServiceAccount Tokens**: In-cluster communication uses Kubernetes ServiceAccount tokens\n- **JWT Signing**: Outbound requests to sandboxes are signed with JWT\n- **API Tokens**: External clients authenticate via bearer tokens\n\n### Authorization\n\n- **RBAC**: Role-based access control for Kubernetes resources\n- **Network Policies**: Pod-level network isolation (future enhancement)\n- **Pod Security**: Sandboxed execution with restricted capabilities\n\n### Network Security\n\n- **TLS**: All external communications encrypted (optional)\n- **Internal mTLS**: Pod-to-pod communication (future enhancement)\n- **Network Policies**: Namespace-level traffic controls\n\n## Scaling Considerations\n\n### Horizontal Scaling\n\n- **Router**: Multiple replicas behind load balancer\n- **Workload Manager**: Single instance with leader election\n- **Session Store**: Redis cluster for high availability\n\n### Vertical Scaling\n\n- **Sandbox Pods**: Resource limits defined per AgentRuntime\n- **Session Timeout**: Configurable session duration (default: 15 minutes)\n- **Idle Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup of idle sessions (15 minutes)\n\n## Failure Modes\n\n| Component | Failure Mode | Impact | Recovery |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|----------|\n| Router | Pod crash | New requests fail | K8s restarts, LB routes to healthy pods |\n| Session Store | Redis down | Sessions lost | New sessions created, existing users reconnect |\n| Workload Manager | Pod crash | Cannot create new agents | K8s restarts, existing agents continue |\n| Sandbox Pod | OOM/Kill | Agent restarts | Session re-created, user may retry |\n\n## Monitoring\n\n### Metrics\n\n- **Request Rate**: Requests per second by endpoint\n- **Latency**: P50, P95, P99 response times\n- **Error Rate**: 4xx and 5xx responses\n- **Session Count**: Active sessions in Redis\n\n### Health Checks\n\n- **Liveness**: `/health/live` - Process is running\n- **Readiness**: `/health/ready` - Service can handle requests\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Client SDK Architecture](/docs/architecture/client-sdk)\n- [Services Architecture](/docs/architecture/services)\n- [Runtime Operations](/docs/architecture/runtime)\n- [Data Flow](/docs/architecture/data-flow)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n