{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887624763,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b26aa38001s2SjyHh9TXzyZk","messageID":"msg_d7b26a1a4001QafQk3pc3nKUXA","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887653055,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b26ac6a00168eVqmjqod9Ken","messageID":"msg_d7b26a1a4001QafQk3pc3nKUXA","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_0a70ed56352b4ea3ad98125d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: client-sdk\ntitle: Client SDK Architecture\ndescription: Architecture of the AgentCube Python SDK clients\nsidebar_position: 2\n---\n\n# Client SDK Architecture\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides programmatic access to AgentCube services. It is built with a layered architecture separating control plane and data plane operations.\n\n## Architecture Diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph \"SDK Layer\"\n        ARC[AgentRuntimeClient]\n        CIC[CodeInterpreterClient]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Client Layer\"\n        subgraph \"Control Plane\"\n            CP[ControlPlaneClient]\n        end\n        subgraph \"Data Plane\"\n            ARDP[AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient]\n            CIDP[CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient]\n        end\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Utilities\"\n        HTTP[HTTP Utilities]\n        Log[Logging]\n        Ex[Exceptions]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"External Services\"\n        Router[Router Service]\n        WorkloadMgr[Workload Manager]\n    end\n    \n    ARC --> ARDP\n    ARC --> HTTP\n    ARC --> Log\n    ARC --> Ex\n    CIC --> CP\n    CIC --> CIDP\n    CIC --> HTTP\n    CIC --> Log\n    CIC --> Ex\n    ARDP --> Router\n    CP --> WorkloadMgr\n    CIDP --> Router\n```\n\n## Client Classes\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` is the primary interface for interacting with agent runtimes. It handles session lifecycle and invocation.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n\n#### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Session Bootstrap**: Creates new sessions via GET request to the invocation endpoint\n2. **Session Reuse**: Supports reusing existing session IDs\n3. **Request Invocation**: Forwards payloads to the Agent Runtime through the Router\n4. **Resource Management**: Manages HTTP session and connection pooling\n\n#### Key Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `router_url` | Base URL of the Router service |\n| `session_id` | Current session identifier |\n| `_session` | `requests.Session` for connection pooling |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for data operations |\n\n#### Initialization Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant ARC as AgentRuntimeClient\n    participant Router\n    participant ARDP as AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n    User->>ARC: __init__(router_url, agent_name, namespace)\n    ARC->>ARC: Validate router_url\n    ARC->>Router: GET /v1/.../invocations/\n    Router-->>ARC: x-agentcube-session-id header\n    ARC->>ARC: Store session_id\n    ARC->>ARDP: __init__(session_id, ...)\n    ARC-->>User: Client ready\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient\n\nThe `CodeInterpreterClient` provides a high-level interface for code execution sessions.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n\n#### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Session Creation**: Creates sessions via Control Plane API\n2. **Command Execution**: Executes commands in the sandbox\n3. **Code Running**: Executes Python code (wraps commands)\n4. **File Operations**: Upload, download, list files\n5. **Session Cleanup**: Properly closes and deletes sessions\n\n#### Key Methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `execute_command()` | Execute a shell command |\n| `run_code()` | Run Python code |\n| `write_file()` | Write file to sandbox |\n| `upload_file()` | Upload local file |\n| `download_file()` | Download remote file |\n| `list_files()` | List sandbox files |\n| `stop()` | Stop and cleanup session |\n\n## Client Layer\n\n### ControlPlaneClient\n\nHandles operations that create/modify infrastructure:\n\n- **Session Management**: Create and delete sessions\n- **Agent Deployment**: Deploy AgentRuntime CRDs (via services)\n\n**File**: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n\n### DataPlaneClient\n\nHandles runtime data operations:\n\n- **Invocation**: Send requests to running agents\n- **Command Execution**: Execute commands in Code Interpreter\n\n**Files**:\n- `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n\n## Connection Management\n\n### HTTP Session Pooling\n\nThe SDK uses `requests.Session` with configurable connection pooling:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.utils.http import create_session\n\nsession = create_session(\n    pool_connections=10,  # Number of connection pools\n    pool_maxsize=10,      # Connections per pool\n)\n```\n\n### Timeout Configuration\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `timeout` | 120s | Read timeout |\n| `connect_timeout` | 5.0s | Connection timeout |\n\nTimeouts can be overridden per-invocation:\n\n```python\nclient.invoke(payload, timeout=30)  # 30 second timeout\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```mermaid\nclassDiagram\n    class AgentCubeError {\n        <<abstract>>\n    }\n    class SessionError {\n        +session_id: str\n    }\n    class DataPlaneError {\n        +status_code: int\n    }\n    class CommandExecutionError {\n        +exit_code: int\n        +stderr: str\n        +command: str\n    }\n    \n    AgentCubeError <|-- SessionError\n    AgentCubeError <|-- DataPlaneError\n    AgentCubeError <|-- CommandExecutionError\n```\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import SessionError, DataPlaneError\n\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\nexcept SessionError as e:\n    print(f\"Session error: {e}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Context Manager Support\n\nBoth clients support Python context managers for automatic resource cleanup:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient\n\n# AgentRuntimeClient\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\") as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\n# Session automatically closed\n\n# CodeInterpreterClient\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\") as ci:\n    result = ci.run_code(\"print('Hello, World!')\")\n# Session automatically stopped\n```\n\n## Configuration Options\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `\"my-agent\"` | Name of the Agent Runtime |\n| `namespace` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | Required | Router service URL |\n| `session_id` | Auto-created | Existing session to reuse |\n| `timeout` | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | 5.0 | Connection timeout in seconds |\n| `pool_connections` | 10 | HTTP pool connections |\n| `pool_maxsize` | 10 | Max connections per pool |\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `router_url` | Required | Router service URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Optional | Workload Manager URL |\n| `auth_token` | Optional | Authentication token |\n| `name` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Session/agent name |\n| `namespace` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | 3600 | Session TTL in seconds |\n| `session_id` | Auto-created | Existing session to reuse |\n\n## Thread Safety\n\nThe clients are **not thread-safe**. Each thread should create its own client instance:\n\n```python\n# Each thread gets its own client\ndef handle_request():\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    try:\n        return client.invoke(payload)\n    finally:\n        client.close()\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [System Design](/docs/architecture/system-design)\n- [Agent Runtime API](/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime)\n- [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter)\n- [Exceptions Reference](/docs/api/sdk-exceptions)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [107:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [135:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [137:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [145:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable to \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":146,"character":61},"end":{"line":146,"character":68}},"message":"Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":152,"character":30},"end":{"line":152,"character":36}},"message":"\"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"","severity":1,"code":"reportOptionalMemberAccess","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportOptionalMemberAccess"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":152,"character":15},"end":{"line":152,"character":72}},"message":"Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"","severity":1,"code":"reportCallIssue","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportCallIssue"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":170,"character":32},"end":{"line":170,"character":36}},"message":"Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAttributeAccessIssue","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAttributeAccessIssue"}}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":96,"character":27},"end":{"line":96,"character":42}},"message":"Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportArgumentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":99,"character":27},"end":{"line":99,"character":43}},"message":"Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportArgumentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":106,"character":58},"end":{"line":106,"character":74}},"message":"Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/confi