{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887699457,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b275c2b001HfXUe3MWQ2cu7i","messageID":"msg_d7b275125001AqgsLd5vJybd0Z","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_69f4c9afe23b4286b34739b5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: services\ntitle: Services Architecture\ndescription: Service layer architecture - MetadataService, DockerService, K8sProvider\nsidebar_position: 3\n---\n\n# Services Architecture\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube service layer provides higher-level abstractions for working with agent runtimes, Docker images, and Kubernetes resources. These services are used by the CLI and can be imported for custom workflows.\n\n## Service Components\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph \"Services\"\n        MP[MetadataService]\n        DS[DockerService]\n        AP[AgentCubeProvider]\n        K8sP[K8sProvider]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Runtime Operations\"\n        Pkg[PackRuntime]\n        Build[BuildRuntime]\n        Pub[PublishRuntime]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Kubernetes\"\n        K8s[Kubernetes API]\n        CRD[Custom Resources]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Container\"\n        Docker[Docker Daemon]\n        Registry[Container Registry]\n    end\n    \n    MP --> Pkg\n    DS --> Build\n    DS --> Pub\n    AP --> Pub\n    K8sP --> Pub\n    Pkg --> MP\n    Build --> DS\n    Pub --> AP\n    Pub --> K8sP\n    AP --> K8s\n    K8sP --> K8s\n    DS --> Docker\n    DS --> Registry\n```\n\n## MetadataService\n\nThe MetadataService handles agent metadata management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Metadata Loading**: Load agent metadata from YAML files\n2. **Metadata Generation**: Generate metadata for agents without existing files\n3. **Validation**: Validate metadata structure and required fields\n4. **Default Values**: Provide sensible defaults for missing fields\n\n### Key Methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `load_metadata()` | Load metadata from file |\n| `generate_metadata()` | Generate metadata from workspace |\n| `validate_metadata()` | Validate metadata structure |\n| `save_metadata()` | Save metadata to file |\n\n### Metadata Schema\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: A helpful assistant\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nresources:\n  limits:\n    cpu: \"1\"\n    memory: 1Gi\nenvironment:\n  KEY: value\n```\n\n## DockerService\n\nThe DockerService handles Docker image building and management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Image Building**: Build Docker images from packed workspaces\n2. **Image Tagging**: Tag images with version and registry\n3. **Image Pushing**: Push images to container registries\n4. **Build Logging**: Stream build logs for debugging\n\n### Key Methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `build_image()` | Build Docker image |\n| `tag_image()` | Tag image for registry |\n| `push_image()` | Push image to registry |\n| `pull_image()` | Pull image from registry |\n| `get_image_id()` | Get image ID |\n| `list_images()` | List local images |\n\n### Build Configuration\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import DockerService\n\ndocker = DockerService()\nresult = docker.build_image(\n    workspace_path=\"./packed\",\n    image_name=\"my-agent\",\n    tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n    dockerfile_path=\"./packed/Dockerfile\",\n)\nprint(f\"Built image: {result['image_id']}\")\n```\n\n## AgentCubeProvider\n\nThe AgentCubeProvider handles AgentRuntime CRD operations.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\n### CRD Details\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Group | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| Version | `v1alpha1` |\n| Plural | `agentruntimes` |\n\n### Key Methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `deploy_agent_runtime()` | Deploy AgentRuntime CR |\n| `get_agent_runtime()` | Get AgentRuntime details |\n| `delete_agent_runtime()` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| `update_agent_runtime()` | Update AgentRuntime |\n\n### Deployment Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"agentcube\")\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    image_url=\"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    port=8080,\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    env_vars={\"DEBUG\": \"true\"},\n)\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {result['endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Spec\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: my-agent\n  namespace: agentcube\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: 8h\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  imagePullSecrets:\n    - name: default-secret\n  targetPorts:\n    - port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      name: http\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: agent\n          image: my-agent:latest\n          resources:\n            limits:\n              cpu: \"1\"\n              memory: 1Gi\n```\n\n## K8sProvider\n\nThe K8sProvider provides generic Kubernetes resource management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Deployment Management**: Create/update/delete standard K8s Deployments\n2. **Service Management**: Create/update/delete K8s Services\n3. **ConfigMap Management**: Manage configuration data\n4. **Secret Management**: Handle sensitive data\n\n### Key Methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `create_deployment()` | Create Deployment |\n| `get_deployment()` | Get Deployment details |\n| `update_deployment()` | Update Deployment |\n| `delete_deployment()` | Delete Deployment |\n| `create_service()` | Create Service |\n| `create_configmap()` | Create ConfigMap |\n| `create_secret()` | Create Secret |\n\n### Deployment Options\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import K8sProvider\n\nk8s = K8sProvider(namespace=\"default\")\nresult = k8s.create_deployment(\n    name=\"my-agent\",\n    image=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    replicas=3,\n    port=8080,\n    node_port=30080,\n)\n```\n\n## Service Configuration\n\n### Kubernetes Configuration\n\nServices support multiple Kubernetes configuration methods:\n\n1. **Kubeconfig File**: Explicit kubeconfig path\n2. **Default Location**: `~/.kube/config`\n3. **In-Cluster**: When running inside a pod\n\n```python\n# Explicit kubeconfig\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(kubeconfig=\"/path/to/kubeconfig\")\n\n# Default (uses ~/.kube/config or in-cluster)\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider()\n\n# In-cluster automatic\n# When running in a pod with service account,\n# kubernetes client loads in-cluster config automatically\n```\n\n### Mock Mode\n\nServices can operate in mock mode when Kubernetes client is unavailable:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=True)\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n    image_url=\"test:latest\",\n    port=8080,\n)\n# Returns mock result without actual K8s API calls\n```\n\n## Integration with Runtime Operations\n\nThe services are used by the runtime operation classes:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"CLI Commands\"\n        Pack[pack]\n        Build[build]\n        Publish[publish]\n        Invoke[invoke]\n        Status[status]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Runtime Classes\"\n        PackRT[PackRuntime]\n        BuildRT[BuildRuntime]\n        PubRT[PublishRuntime]\n        InvRT[InvokeRuntime]\n        StatRT[StatusRuntime]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Services\"\n        MP[MetadataService]\n        DS[DockerService]\n        AP[AgentCubeProvider]\n        K8sP[K8sProvider]\n    end\n    \n    Pack --> PackRT\n    Build --> BuildRT\n    Publish --> PubRT\n    Invoke --> InvRT\n    Status --> StatRT\n    \n    PackRT --> MP\n    BuildRT --> DS\n    PubRT --> DS\n    PubRT --> AP\n    PubRT --> K8sP\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\nServices raise exceptions on failure:\n\n| Exception | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid parameters |\n| `KubernetesError` | K8s operation failed |\n| `DockerError` | Docker operation failed |\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [System Design](/docs/architecture/system-design)\n- [Runtime Operations](/docs/architecture/runtime)\n- [CLI Reference](/docs/api/sdk-cli)\n- [Services API](/docs/api/sdk-services)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/architecture/services.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type