{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887739765,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b27d957001iwpIcLk6cdZg9P","messageID":"msg_d7b27ce27001Tz6Uq8iDr3wut4","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_e2187d4f10ac4ae1a547c931","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: runtime\ntitle: Runtime Operations Architecture\ndescription: Architecture of runtime operations - Pack, Build, Publish, Invoke, Status\nsidebar_position: 4\n---\n\n# Runtime Operations Architecture\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube CLI provides five main runtime operations that form the agent deployment workflow. These operations are implemented as separate classes that handle the end-to-end lifecycle of deploying and invoking agents.\n\n## Operations Overview\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"Deployment Workflow\"\n        P[pack]\n        B[build]\n        Pub[publish]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Runtime Workflow\"\n        I[invoke]\n        S[status]\n    end\n    \n    P --> B\n    B --> Pub\n    Pub --> I\n    Pub --> S\n    \n    subgraph \"Classes\"\n        PR[PackRuntime]\n        BR[BuildRuntime]\n        PubR[PublishRuntime]\n        IR[InvokeRuntime]\n        SR[StatusRuntime]\n    end\n    \n    PR -.-> P\n    BR -.-> B\n    PubR -.-> Pub\n    IR -.-> I\n    SR -.-> S\n```\n\n## Pack Runtime\n\nThe PackRuntime operation prepares an agent workspace for deployment.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Workspace Validation**: Validate workspace structure and required files\n2. **Metadata Management**: Load or generate agent metadata\n3. **Dependency Processing**: Handle dependencies (pip, npm, etc.)\n4. **Dockerfile Generation**: Generate Dockerfile if not present\n5. **Output Packaging**: Create packaged workspace for build\n\n### Workflow\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[Start: workspace path] --> B{Valid workspace?}\n    B -->|No| C[Validate Structure]\n    B -->|Yes| D{metadata.yaml exists?}\n    C --> E[Error: Invalid workspace]\n    D -->|No| F[Generate metadata]\n    D -->|Yes| G[Load metadata]\n    F --> H{Dependencies?}\n    G --> H\n    H -->|Yes| I[Process dependencies]\n    H -->|No| J{Dockerfile exists?}\n    I --> J\n    J -->|No| K[Generate Dockerfile]\n    J -->|Yes| L[Use existing]\n    K --> M[Create output package]\n    L --> M\n    M --> N[End: packed workspace]\n```\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `workspace_path` | Path to agent workspace | `\".\"` |\n| `agent_name` | Override agent name | Auto-detect |\n| `language` | Programming language | Auto-detect |\n| `entrypoint` | Override entrypoint | From metadata |\n| `port` | Port to expose | `8080` |\n| `build_mode` | Build strategy | `\"local\"` |\n| `description` | Agent description | From metadata |\n| `output` | Output path | `./agentcube-pack` |\n\n### Output\n\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"workspace_path\": \"/path/to/workspace\",\n    \"output_path\": \"/path/to/output\",\n    \"metadata_file\": \"/path/to/metadata.yaml\",\n    \"dockerfile_generated\": True,\n}\n```\n\n## Build Runtime\n\nThe BuildRuntime operation builds Docker images from packed workspaces.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Docker Build**: Build Docker image from packed workspace\n2. **Image Tagging**: Tag image with version\n3. **Metadata Extraction**: Extract metadata from packed workspace\n4. **Build Output**: Return build artifacts\n\n### Workflow\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[Start: packed workspace] --> B[Load metadata]\n    B --> C[Find Dockerfile]\n    C --> D{Build mode}\n    D -->|local| E[Docker build]\n    D -->|cloud| F[Cloud build API]\n    E --> G[Tag image]\n    F --> G\n    G --> H[Return build result]\n```\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `workspace_path` | Path to packed workspace | Required |\n| `proxy` | Custom proxy URL | None |\n| `cloud_provider` | Cloud provider name | None |\n| `output` | Output path | None |\n| `verbose` | Enable verbose logging | False |\n\n### Build Modes\n\n| Mode | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `local` | Build using local Docker daemon |\n| `cloud` | Build using cloud provider build service |\n\n### Output\n\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"image_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"image_tag\": \"v1.0.0\",\n    \"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n    \"version\": \"v1.0.0\",\n}\n```\n\n## Publish Runtime\n\nThe PublishRuntime operation deploys agents to the target provider.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n### Providers\n\n| Provider | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `agentcube` | Deploy via AgentRuntime CRD |\n| `k8s` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes resources |\n\n### AgentCube Provider\n\nDeploys using the AgentRuntime custom resource:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"agentcube\")\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    image_url=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    port=8080,\n)\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Provider\n\nDeploys using standard Kubernetes resources:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import K8sProvider\n\nprovider = K8sProvider(namespace=\"default\")\nresult = provider.create_deployment(\n    name=\"my-agent\",\n    image=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    replicas=3,\n    port=8080,\n    node_port=30080,\n)\n```\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `workspace_path` | Path to workspace | `\".\"` |\n| `version` | Semantic version | Auto |\n| `image_url` | Image repository URL | Auto |\n| `image_username` | Registry username | None |\n| `image_password` | Registry password | None |\n| `description` | Agent description | None |\n| `region` | Deployment region | None |\n| `cloud_provider` | Cloud provider | None |\n| `provider` | Target provider | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `node_port` | NodePort (30000-32767) | None |\n| `replicas` | Number of replicas | 1 |\n| `namespace` | Kubernetes namespace | `\"default\"` |\n\n### Output\n\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n    \"endpoint\": \"http://my-agent.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n    \"status\": \"deployed\",\n}\n```\n\n## Invoke Runtime\n\nThe InvokeRuntime operation sends requests to deployed agents.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Endpoint Resolution**: Find agent endpoint from workspace metadata\n2. **Payload Preparation**: Prepare JSON payload\n3. **HTTP Request**: Send request to agent\n4. **Response Handling**: Parse and return response\n\n### Providers\n\n| Provider | Endpoint Resolution |\n|----------|---------------------|\n| `agentcube` | Query AgentRuntime CR |\n| `k8s` | Query Service |\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `workspace_path` | Path to workspace | `\".\"` |\n| `payload` | JSON input | `\"{}\"` |\n| `header_list` | Custom headers | None |\n| `provider` | Target provider | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `verbose` | Enable verbose logging | False |\n\n### Usage\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n```\n\n### Output\n\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"payload\": {\"message\": \"Hello!\"},\n    \"response\": {\"response\": \"Hello back!\", \"status\": \"success\"},\n}\n```\n\n## Status Runtime\n\nThe StatusRuntime operation checks the status of deployed agents.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n1. **Endpoint Resolution**: Find agent from workspace metadata\n2. **Status Query**: Query agent status from provider\n3. **Status Formatting**: Format status for display\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `workspace_path` | Path to workspace | `\".\"` |\n| `provider` | Target provider | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `verbose` | Enable verbose logging | False |\n\n### Usage\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube status\n```\n\n### Output\n\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"agent_id\": \"agent-abc123\",\n    \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n    \"status\": \"Running\",\n    \"endpoint\": \"http://my-agent.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n    \"namespace\": \"agentcube\",\n}\n```\n\n## Deployment Flow Diagram\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI\n    participant Pack\n    participant Build\n    participant Publish\n    participant K8s\n    \n    User->>CLI: kubectl agentcube pack\n    CLI->>Pack: pack(workspace)\n    Pack-->>CLI: packed workspace\n    CLI->>User: Pack complete\n    \n    User->>CLI: kubectl agentcube build\n    CLI->>Build: build(workspace)\n    Build->>Build: docker build\n    Build-->>CLI: image details\n    CLI->>User: Build complete\n    \n    User->>CLI: kubectl agentcube publish\n    CLI->>Publish: publish(workspace)\n    Publish->>K8s: create deployment\n    K8s-->>Publish: deployment info\n    Publish-->>CLI: endpoint\n    CLI->>User: Published\n    \n    User->>CLI: kubectl agentcube invoke\n    CLI->>CLI: resolve endpoint\n    CLI->>K8s: POST request\n    K8s-->>CLI: response\n    CLI->>User: Response\n    \n    User->>CLI: kubectl agentcube status\n    CLI->>CLI: resolve endpoint\n    CLI->>K8s: get status\n    K8s-->>CLI: status\n    CLI->>User: Status table\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Services Architecture](/docs/architecture/services)\n- [CLI Reference](/docs/api/sdk-cli)\n- [Pack Runtime API](/docs/api/sdk-runtime)\n- [Quick Start Guide](/docs/getting-started/quickstart)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailia