{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887779454,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b287db8002rUR2s9OTl7WRK8","messageID":"msg_d7b286bb1001DrBA9tICJIMb40","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_741c053cbe3f4189a6597559","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: data-flow\ntitle: Data Flow Diagrams\ndescription: Data flow and sequence diagrams for AgentCube operations\nsidebar_position: 5\n---\n\n# Data Flow Diagrams\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document illustrates the data flow through the AgentCube system, showing how requests move from clients through various components to reach agent runtimes.\n\n## Request-Response Flow\n\n### Agent Invocation Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client\n    participant Router\n    participant SessionStore\n    participant WorkloadManager\n    participant Sandbox\n\n    Note over Client,Sandbox: New Session Flow\n    Client->>Router: POST /v1/namespaces/:ns/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\n    Router->>Router: Extract session ID from header\n    alt No session ID\n        Router->>Router: Check if session exists in store\n        Router->>WorkloadManager: POST /v1/agent-runtime\n        WorkloadManager->>WorkloadManager: Create AgentRuntime CR\n        WorkloadManager-->>Router: {sessionId, endpoints}\n        Router->>SessionStore: Store SandboxInfo\n        Router->>SessionStore: Set last-activity-time\n        Router->>Client: 200 OK + x-agentcube-session-id\n    else Session exists\n        Router->>SessionStore: Get SandboxInfo by session_id\n        SessionStore-->>Router: SandboxInfo\n        Router->>SessionStore: Update last-activity-time\n    end\n\n    Note over Client,Sandbox: Request Proxy Flow\n    Router->>Router: Determine upstream URL\n    Router->>Router: Set forwarding headers\n    alt Sandbox kind is Sandbox/SandboxClaim\n        Router->>Router: Generate JWT token\n    end\n    Router->>Sandbox: Proxy request with JWT\n    Sandbox-->>Router: Response\n    Router->>SessionStore: Update last-activity-time (post-request)\n    Router->>Client: 200 OK + x-agentcube-session-id\n```\n\n### Code Interpreter Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client\n    participant Router\n    participant SessionStore\n    participant ControlPlane\n    participant CodeInterpreter\n\n    Note over Client,CodeInterpreter: Create Session Flow\n    Client->>Router: POST /v1/namespaces/:ns/code-interpreters/:name/invocations\n    Router->>Router: Extract session ID\n    alt No session ID\n        Router->>ControlPlane: POST /v1/sessions\n        ControlPlane->>ControlPlane: Create CodeInterpreter CR\n        ControlPlane-->>Router: {sessionId, endpoints}\n        Router->>SessionStore: Store SandboxInfo\n        Router->>Client: 200 OK + x-agentcube-session-id\n    end\n\n    Note over Client,CodeInterpreter: Execute Command Flow\n    Client->>Router: POST with command\n    Router->>SessionStore: Get SandboxInfo\n    SessionStore-->>Router: SandboxInfo\n    Router->>CodeInterpreter: Proxy command execution\n    CodeInterpreter-->>Router: {stdout, stderr, exit_code}\n    Router->>Client: 200 OK\n```\n\n## Session Management Flow\n\n### Session Creation\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[Client Request] --> B{Session ID in header?}\n    B -->|No| C[Create New Session]\n    B -->|Yes| D[Lookup Session]\n    \n    C --> E[Workload Manager: Create Sandbox]\n    E --> F[Kubernetes: Provision Pod]\n    F --> G[Pod Ready]\n    G --> H[Router: Get Endpoint]\n    H --> I[Session Store: Save Session]\n    I --> J[Return Session ID]\n    \n    D --> K{Session in Store?}\n    K -->|Yes| L[Get Sandbox Info]\n    K -->|No| M[Error: Session Not Found]\n    L --> N[Proxy to Sandbox]\n    N --> O[Update Last Activity]\n    O --> P[Return Response]\n    \n    J --> Q[Client: Session ID]\n    M --> R[Client: 404 Error]\n    P --> Q\n```\n\n### Idle Cleanup Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Controller\n    participant K8s\n    participant Sandbox\n\n    loop Reconciliation Loop\n        Controller->>K8s: List Sandboxes\n        K8s-->>Controller: Sandbox list\n        \n        Controller->>Controller: For each Sandbox\n        Controller->>K8s: Get Sandbox\n        K8s-->>Controller: Sandbox object\n        \n        alt Has last-activity-time annotation\n            Controller->>Controller: Parse RFC3339 timestamp\n            Controller->>Controller: Calculate expiration\n            alt Time exceeded 15 minutes\n                Controller->>K8s: Delete Sandbox\n                K8s-->>Controller: Deleted\n            else Not expired\n                Controller->>Controller: Requeue until expiration\n            end\n        else No annotation\n            Controller->>Controller: Skip (no action)\n        end\n    end\n```\n\n## Data Plane Communication\n\n### HTTP Request Flow\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n    subgraph Client\n        SDK[Python SDK]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph Router\n        LB[Load Balancer]\n        Gin[Gin Handler]\n        Proxy[Reverse Proxy]\n        JWT[JWT Generator]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph Upstream\n        Sandbox[Sandbox Pod]\n    end\n    \n    SDK -->|HTTP Request| LB\n    LB -->|Route| Gin\n    Gin -->|Lookup Session| Redis\n    Gin -->|Generate Token| JWT\n    JWT -->|Add Header| Proxy\n    Proxy -->|Forward| Sandbox\n    Sandbox -->|Response| Proxy\n    Proxy -->|Response| Gin\n    Gin -->|Response| LB\n    LB -->|HTTP Response| SDK\n```\n\n### Header Propagation\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client\n    participant Router\n    participant Sandbox\n\n    Client->>Router: GET /path Header: X-Forwarded-For, Host\n    \n    Router->>Router: Process Headers\n    Note over Router: X-Forwarded-Host = Client.Host<br/>X-Forwarded-Proto = http/https<br/>X-Forwarded-For = append(Client.IP)\n    \n    Router->>Sandbox: GET /path<br/>X-Forwarded-For: ...<br/>X-Forwarded-Host: ...<br/>X-Forwarded-Proto: ...<br/>Authorization: Bearer \\<jwt\\>\n    \n    Sandbox-->>Router: Response\n    \n    Router->>Router: Add Response Header\n    Note over Router: x-agentcube-session-id = session_id\n    \n    Router->>Client: Response<br/>x-agentcube-session-id: session_id\n```\n\n## Error Flow\n\n### Error Mapping\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[Proxy Error] --> B{Error Type}\n    \n    B -->|connection refused| C[502 Bad Gateway]\n    B -->|timeout| D[504 Gateway Timeout]\n    B -->|other| E[502 Bad Gateway]\n    \n    C --> F[JSON: {\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}]\n    D --> G[JSON: {\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}]\n    E --> F\n    \n    F --> H[Client receives error]\n    G --> H\n```\n\n### Session Error Handling\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[Session Operation] --> B{Result}\n    \n    B -->|Success| C[Continue]\n    B -->|NotFound| D[Return 404]\n    B -->|Network Error| E[Return 502]\n    B -->|Timeout| F[Return 504]\n    \n    D --> G[Client: SessionError]\n    E --> H[Client: DataPlaneError]\n    F --> I[Client: DataPlaneError]\n```\n\n## Connection Management\n\n### Session Pool\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TB\n    subgraph \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n        Session[requests.Session]\n        Pool[Connection Pool]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"HTTP Pool\"\n        PC[pool_connections: 10]\n        PMS[pool_maxsize: 10]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph \"Timeouts\"\n        CT[connect_timeout: 5.0s]\n        RT[timeout: 120s]\n    end\n    \n    Session --> Pool\n    Pool --> PC\n    Pool --> PMS\n    Session --> CT\n    Session --> RT\n```\n\n## State Management\n\n### Session State\n\n```mermaid\nerDiagram\n    SESSION ||--|| SANDBOX_INFO : contains\n    SESSION {\n        string session_id PK\n        string sandbox_id\n        string name\n        string namespace\n        string kind\n        string entrypoint\n        timestamp created_at\n        timestamp last_activity_at\n    }\n    \n    SANDBOX_INFO {\n        string sandbox_id\n        string name\n        string namespace\n        string session_id\n        list entrypoints\n    }\n    \n    SESSION ||--o| LAST_ACTIVITY : tracks\n    LAST_ACTIVITY {\n        string session_id FK\n        timestamp last_activity_time\n    }\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [System Design](/docs/architecture/system-design)\n- [Client SDK Architecture](/docs/architecture/client-sdk)\n- [Services Architecture](/docs/architecture/services)\n- [Session Routing Specification](/session-routing/spec)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100