{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887822822,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2944a20014gU7EVjTn503jx","messageID":"msg_d7b2930aa001AiJHdUEMl7lAfc","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_fd0ebb6b68b544178708c08f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-agent-runtime\ntitle: AgentRuntimeClient SDK API\ndescription: Complete API reference for AgentRuntimeClient\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# AgentRuntimeClient SDK API\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` provides a high-level interface for interacting with Agent Runtime through the AgentCube Router. It handles session lifecycle management and request invocation.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n\n## Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n```\n\n## Constructor\n\n```python\nAgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name: str = \"my-agent\",\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    timeout: int = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT,\n    connect_timeout: float = DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT,\n    pool_connections: int = DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS,\n    pool_maxsize: int = DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE,\n)\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | `\"my-agent\"` | Name of the Agent Runtime |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router service URL |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session to reuse |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Read timeout in seconds |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout in seconds |\n| `pool_connections` | `int` | `10` | Number of HTTP connection pools |\n| `pool_maxsize` | `int` | `10` | Max connections per pool |\n\n### Raises\n\n- `ValueError`: If `router_url` is not provided and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is not set.\n\n### Example\n\n```python\n# Using environment variable\nimport os\nos.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = \"http://localhost:8081\"\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"agentcube\"\n)\n\n# Using explicit URL\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"agentcube\"\n)\n```\n\n## Methods\n\n### invoke\n\n```python\nclient.invoke(\n    payload: dict,\n    timeout: Optional[Union[int, tuple[float, float]]] = None\n) -> dict\n```\n\nInvokes the Agent Runtime with the given payload.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `payload` | `dict` | Required | JSON payload to send to the agent |\n| `timeout` | `Optional[Union[int, tuple[float, float]]]` | `None` | Timeout in seconds or (connect, read) tuple |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`dict` - Response from the Agent Runtime containing the response data.\n\n#### Raises\n\n- `ValueError`: If session is not initialized.\n- `DataPlaneError`: If the invocation fails.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n\nresponse = client.invoke({\n    \"message\": \"Hello, agent!\",\n    \"context\": {\"user_id\": \"123\"}\n})\n\nprint(response.get(\"response\"))\n```\n\n### close\n\n```python\nclient.close() -> None\n```\n\nCloses the client and releases all resources. This method should be called when done with the client to properly clean up HTTP sessions.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\ntry:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\n    print(response)\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n```\n\n### Context Manager\n\nThe client supports Python's context manager protocol for automatic resource cleanup:\n\n```python\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\") as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\n    print(response)\n# Automatically closed when exiting the block\n```\n\n## Properties\n\n### session_id\n\n```python\nclient.session_id -> Optional[str]\n```\n\nReturns the current session ID. This can be used to reuse the same session across multiple client instances.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nsession_id = client.session_id\n\n# Reuse session in another client\nclient2 = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    session_id=session_id\n)\n```\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | Default read timeout in seconds |\n| `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT` | `5.0` | Default connection timeout in seconds |\n| `DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS` | `10` | Default number of connection pools |\n| `DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE` | `10` | Default max connections per pool |\n\n## Full Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import SessionError, DataPlaneError\n\n# Initialize client\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"agentcube\",\n    timeout=60,\n    connect_timeout=10.0,\n    verbose=True\n)\n\ntry:\n    # Invoke agent with payload\n    response = client.invoke({\n        \"message\": \"What is the weather?\",\n        \"temperature\": 0.7,\n        \"max_tokens\": 500\n    })\n    \n    print(f\"Response: {response.get('response')}\")\n    print(f\"Session ID: {client.session_id}\")\n    \nexcept SessionError as e:\n    print(f\"Session error: {e}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Base URL of the Router service (used when `router_url` is not provided) |\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe client raises specific exceptions for different error conditions:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import (\n    AgentCubeError,\n    SessionError,\n    DataPlaneError\n)\n\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://invalid-url\")\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"test\"})\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    # Invalid parameters\n    print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\nexcept SessionError as e:\n    # Session-related errors (bootstrap, not found)\n    print(f\"Session error: {e}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    # Data plane errors (invocation failures)\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    # Base exception\n    print(f\"AgentCube error: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Thread Safety\n\nThe client is **not thread-safe**. Each thread should create its own instance:\n\n```python\n# Recommended: Each thread creates its own client\nimport threading\n\ndef handle_request(request_id):\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    try:\n        response = client.invoke({\"request_id\": request_id})\n        return response\n    finally:\n        client.close()\n\nthreads = [threading.Thread(target=handle_request, args=(i,)) for i in range(10)]\nfor t in threads:\n    t.start()\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter)\n- [Exceptions Reference](/docs/api/sdk-exceptions)\n- [Client SDK Architecture](/docs/architecture/client-sdk)\n- [Data Flow](/docs/architecture/data-flow)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [107:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [135:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [137:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [145:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable to \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bail