{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887863834,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b29bbfc0019RCuYORE59Bass","messageID":"msg_d7b29b01b001Y681zU6gDdnhk1","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_da58066808844cc9bbfdccd2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-code-interpreter\ntitle: CodeInterpreterClient SDK API\ndescription: Complete API reference for CodeInterpreterClient\nsidebar_position: 2\n---\n\n# CodeInterpreterClient SDK API\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `CodeInterpreterClient` provides a high-level interface for executing code in isolated sandbox environments. It handles session creation, command execution, file operations, and session cleanup.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n\n## Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n```\n\n## Constructor\n\n```python\nCodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n    name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    ttl: int = 3600,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n)\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router service URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n| `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Authentication token |\n| `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Session/agent name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds (1 hour) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Existing session to reuse |\n\n### Raises\n\n- `ValueError`: If `router_url` is not provided and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is not set.\n\n### Example\n\n```python\n# Create new session\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n    name=\"my-session\",\n    namespace=\"agentcube\"\n)\n\n# Reuse existing session\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n)\n```\n\n## Methods\n\n### execute_command\n\n```python\nclient.execute_command(\n    command: str,\n    timeout: Optional[int] = None\n) -> Dict\n```\n\nExecutes a shell command in the Code Interpreter sandbox.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `command` | `str` | Required | Shell command to execute |\n| `timeout` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Timeout in seconds |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`Dict` - Response containing:\n- `stdout`: Standard output\n- `stderr`: Standard error\n- `exit_code`: Exit code (0 for success)\n\n#### Raises\n\n- `CommandExecutionError`: If the command returns a non-zero exit code.\n- `DataPlaneError`: If the execution fails.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nresult = client.execute_command(\"ls -la /workspace\")\nprint(result[\"stdout\"])\nprint(f\"Exit code: {result['exit_code']}\")\n```\n\n### run_code\n\n```python\nclient.run_code(\n    code: str,\n    language: str = \"python\",\n    timeout: Optional[int] = None\n) -> Dict\n```\n\nRuns code in the Code Interpreter. Currently only Python is supported.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `code` | `str` | Required | Code to run |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language (python, py, python3) |\n| `timeout` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Timeout in seconds |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`Dict` - Response containing execution result.\n\n#### Raises\n\n- `ValueError`: If the language is not supported.\n- `CommandExecutionError`: If the code returns a non-zero exit code.\n- `DataPlaneError`: If execution fails.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n\n# Run Python code\nresult = client.run_code(\"\"\"\nimport sys\nprint(f\"Python version: {sys.version}\")\nresult = sum(range(100))\nprint(f\"Sum of 0-99: {result}\")\n\"\"\")\n\nprint(result[\"stdout\"])\n```\n\n### write_file\n\n```python\nclient.write_file(\n    content: str,\n    remote_path: str,\n    mode: str = \"0644\"\n) -> Dict\n```\n\nWrites content to a file in the sandbox.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `content` | `str` | Required | File content |\n| `remote_path` | `str` | Required | Remote file path |\n| `mode` | `str` | `\"0644\"` | File permissions (octal) |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`Dict` - Response containing write result.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n\nclient.write_file(\"#!/usr/bin/env python\\nprint('Hello!')\", \"/tmp/script.py\")\n```\n\n### upload_file\n\n```python\nclient.upload_file(\n    local_path: str,\n    remote_path: str\n) -> Dict\n```\n\nUploads a local file to the sandbox.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `local_path` | `str` | Required | Local file path |\n| `remote_path` | `str` | Required | Remote destination path |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`Dict` - Response containing upload result.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nclient.upload_file(\"./data.json\", \"/workspace/data.json\")\n```\n\n### download_file\n\n```python\nclient.download_file(\n    remote_path: str,\n    local_path: str\n) -> None\n```\n\nDownloads a file from the sandbox to local filesystem.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `remote_path` | `str` | Required | Remote file path |\n| `local_path` | `str` | Required | Local destination path |\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nclient.download_file(\"/workspace/output.txt\", \"./output.txt\")\n```\n\n### list_files\n\n```python\nclient.list_files(path: str = \".\") -> Dict\n```\n\nLists files in the sandbox directory.\n\n#### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `path` | `str` | `\".\"` | Directory path to list |\n\n#### Returns\n\n`Dict` - Response containing file listing.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nresult = client.list_files(\"/workspace\")\nfor file in result.get(\"files\", []):\n    print(file[\"name\"], file[\"size\"])\n```\n\n### stop\n\n```python\nclient.stop() -> None\n```\n\nStops the Code Interpreter session and releases resources. If a new session was created, it will be deleted. If an existing session was provided, it will be preserved.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\ntry:\n    result = client.run_code(\"print('Hello')\")\n    print(result)\nfinally:\n    client.stop()\n```\n\n### Context Manager\n\nThe client supports Python's context manager protocol:\n\n```python\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\") as client:\n    result = client.run_code(\"print('Hello, World!')\")\n    print(result)\n# Session automatically stopped\n```\n\n## Properties\n\n### session_id\n\n```python\nclient.session_id -> Optional[str]\n```\n\nReturns the current session ID.\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\nprint(f\"Session: {client.session_id}\")\n```\n\n## Full Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import (\n    CommandExecutionError,\n    DataPlaneError\n)\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n    name=\"data-processor\",\n    namespace=\"agentcube\",\n    ttl=3600,\n    verbose=True\n) as client:\n    \n    # Upload input file\n    client.upload_file(\"./input.csv\", \"/workspace/input.csv\")\n    \n    # Run Python processing script\n    result = client.run_code(\"\"\"\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv('/workspace/input.csv')\nsummary = df.describe()\nsummary.to_csv('/workspace/output.csv')\nprint('Processing complete')\n\"\"\")\n    \n    print(result[\"stdout\"])\n    \n    # Download result\n    client.download_file(\"/workspace/output.csv\", \"./output.csv\")\n    \n    # List files\n    files = client.list_files(\"/workspace\")\n    print(\"Files:\", files)\n    \nprint(\"Session closed\")\n```\n\n## Session Lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Created: Client created\n    Created --> Session: Create session via Control Plane\n    Session --> Ready: Data plane connected\n    Ready --> Executing: execute_command/run_code\n    Executing --> Ready: Command complete\n    Ready --> Stopped: stop() called\n    Session --> Deleted: Session cleanup\n    Deleted --> [*]\n    Stopped --> [*]\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import (\n    AgentCubeError,\n    CommandExecutionError,\n    DataPlaneError\n)\n\ntry:\n    client = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    result = client.execute_command(\"invalid-command\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    print(f\"Command failed: {e}\")\n    print(f\"Exit code: {e.exit_code}\")\n    print(f\"Stderr: {e.stderr}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    print(f\"AgentCube error: {e}\")\nfinally:\n    if 'client' in locals():\n        client.stop()\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Base URL of the Router service |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Base URL of the Workload Manager |\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Agent Runtime API](/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime)\n- [Exceptions Reference](/docs/api/sdk-exceptions)\n- [Client SDK Architecture](/docs/architecture/client-sdk)\n- [Data Flow](/docs/architecture/data-flow)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [107:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [135:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [137:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [145:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable to \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":146,"character":61},"end":{"line":146,"character":68}},"message":"Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":152,"character":30},"end":{"line":152,"character":36}},"message":"\"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"","severity":1,"code":"reportOptionalMemberAccess","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportOptionalMemberAccess"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":152,"character":15},"end":{"line":152,"character":72}},"message":"Argument missing for