{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887908614,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2a5b2f001cJr1zibrPJCHmN","messageID":"msg_d7b2a504b001Ti6Ph64uphIrhI","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f72b3c3fc62c452e91340865","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-services\ntitle: Services API\ndescription: Complete API reference for service layer classes\nsidebar_position: 3\n---\n\n# Services API\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube service layer provides higher-level abstractions for working with agent runtimes, Docker images, and Kubernetes resources. These services are used by the CLI and can be imported for custom workflows.\n\n## MetadataService\n\nHandles agent metadata management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import MetadataService\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nMetadataService(verbose: bool = False)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### load_metadata\n\n```python\nservice.load_metadata(workspace_path: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nLoads metadata from a workspace's metadata.yaml file.\n\n#### generate_metadata\n\n```python\nservice.generate_metadata(\n    workspace_path: str,\n    agent_name: str,\n    language: str,\n    entrypoint: str,\n    port: int = 8080,\n    description: str = \"\",\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nGenerates metadata for an agent workspace.\n\n#### validate_metadata\n\n```python\nservice.validate_metadata(metadata: Dict[str, Any]) -> bool\n```\n\nValidates metadata structure.\n\n#### save_metadata\n\n```python\nservice.save_metadata(\n    metadata: Dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str\n) -> None\n```\n\nSaves metadata to a YAML file.\n\n## DockerService\n\nHandles Docker image building and management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import DockerService\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nDockerService(verbose: bool = False)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### build_image\n\n```python\nservice.build_image(\n    workspace_path: str,\n    image_name: str,\n    tag: str = \"latest\",\n    dockerfile_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    nocache: bool = False,\n    pull: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nBuilds a Docker image from a packed workspace.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | Path to workspace |\n| `image_name` | `str` | Image name |\n| `tag` | `str` | Image tag |\n| `dockerfile_path` | `Optional[str]` | Custom Dockerfile path |\n| `build_args` | `Optional[Dict[str, str]]` | Build arguments |\n| `nocache` | `bool` | Disable build cache |\n| `pull` | `bool` | Always pull base image |\n\n**Returns**: `{image_name, image_tag, image_id}`\n\n#### tag_image\n\n```python\nservice.tag_image(\n    source_image: str,\n    target_repository: str,\n    target_tag: str\n) -> None\n```\n\nTags an image for a registry.\n\n#### push_image\n\n```python\nservice.push_image(\n    image: str,\n    username: Optional[str] = None,\n    password: Optional[str] = None,\n    registry: Optional[str] = None\n) -> None\n```\n\nPushes an image to a container registry.\n\n#### pull_image\n\n```python\nservice.pull_image(\n    image: str,\n    username: Optional[str] = None,\n    password: Optional[str] = None\n) -> None\n```\n\nPulls an image from a registry.\n\n#### get_image_id\n\n```python\nservice.get_image_id(image: str) -> Optional[str]\n```\n\nReturns the image ID for a given image reference.\n\n#### list_images\n\n```python\nservice.list_images(\n    filter: Optional[str] = None,\n    limit: int = 100\n) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]\n```\n\nLists local Docker images.\n\n## AgentCubeProvider\n\nHandles AgentRuntime CRD operations.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nAgentCubeProvider(\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None\n)\n```\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `kubeconfig` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path to kubeconfig |\n\n### CRD Constants\n\n| Constant | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| `CR_GROUP` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` |\n| `CR_VERSION` | `\"v1alpha1\"` |\n| `CR_PLURAL` | `\"agentruntimes\"` |\n\n### Methods\n\n#### deploy_agent_runtime\n\n```python\nprovider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nDeploys an AgentRuntime to Kubernetes.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent name |\n| `image_url` | `str` | Container image URL |\n| `port` | `int` | Port to expose |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | Entrypoint command |\n| `env_vars` | `Optional[Dict[str, str]]` | Environment variables |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | Workload Manager URL |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | Router URL |\n\n**Returns**: `{name, namespace, endpoint, env_vars}`\n\n#### get_agent_runtime\n\n```python\nprovider.get_agent_runtime(\n    name: str,\n    namespace: str\n) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n```\n\nGets an AgentRuntime resource.\n\n#### delete_agent_runtime\n\n```python\nprovider.delete_agent_runtime(\n    name: str,\n    namespace: Optional[str] = None\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nDeletes an AgentRuntime resource.\n\n## K8sProvider\n\nProvides generic Kubernetes resource management.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import K8sProvider\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nK8sProvider(\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None\n)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### create_deployment\n\n```python\nprovider.create_deployment(\n    name: str,\n    image: str,\n    replicas: int = 1,\n    port: int = 8080,\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    resources: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nCreates a standard Kubernetes Deployment.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | Deployment name |\n| `image` | `str` | Container image |\n| `replicas` | `int` | Number of replicas |\n| `port` | `int` | Container port |\n| `node_port` | `Optional[int]` | NodePort (30000-32767) |\n| `env_vars` | `Optional[Dict[str, str]]` | Environment variables |\n| `resources` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | Resource limits |\n\n**Returns**: `{name, namespace, replicas, endpoint}`\n\n#### get_deployment\n\n```python\nprovider.get_deployment(name: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n```\n\nGets a Deployment resource.\n\n#### update_deployment\n\n```python\nprovider.update_deployment(\n    name: str,\n    image: Optional[str] = None,\n    replicas: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nUpdates a Deployment.\n\n#### delete_deployment\n\n```python\nprovider.delete_deployment(name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nDeletes a Deployment.\n\n#### create_service\n\n```python\nprovider.create_service(\n    name: str,\n    port: int,\n    target_port: int = 8080,\n    service_type: str = \"ClusterIP\",\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nCreates a Kubernetes Service.\n\n#### create_configmap\n\n```python\nprovider.create_configmap(\n    name: str,\n    data: Dict[str, str],\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nCreates a ConfigMap.\n\n#### create_secret\n\n```python\nprovider.create_secret(\n    name: str,\n    data: Dict[str, bytes],\n    secret_type: str = \"Opaque\",\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nCreates a Secret.\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Deploy AgentRuntime\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"agentcube\", verbose=True)\n\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    image_url=\"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    port=8080,\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    env_vars={\n        \"DEBUG\": \"true\",\n        \"LOG_LEVEL\": \"info\"\n    },\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workloadmanager:8080\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8081\"\n)\n\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {result['endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n### Build and Push Docker Image\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import DockerService\n\ndocker = DockerService(verbose=True)\n\n# Build\nbuild_result = docker.build_image(\n    workspace_path=\"./packed\",\n    image_name=\"my-agent\",\n    tag=\"v1.0.0\"\n)\nprint(f\"Image ID: {build_result['image_id']}\")\n\n# Tag for registry\ndocker.tag_image(\n    source_image=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    target_repository=\"registry.example.com/my-agent\",\n    target_tag=\"v1.0.0\"\n)\n\n# Push\ndocker.push_image(\n    image=\"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    username=\"user\",\n    password=\"pass\"\n)\n```\n\n### Deploy to Standard Kubernetes\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import K8sProvider\n\nk8s = K8sProvider(namespace=\"default\")\n\n# Create deployment\nresult = k8s.create_deployment(\n    name=\"my-agent\",\n    image=\"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n    replicas=3,\n    port=8080,\n    node_port=30080,\n    env_vars={\"ENV\": \"production\"},\n    resources={\n        \"limits\": {\"cpu\": \"1\", \"memory\": \"1Gi\"},\n        \"requests\": {\"cpu\": \"500m\", \"memory\": \"512Mi\"}\n    }\n)\n\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {result['endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n## Mock Mode\n\nServices can operate in mock mode when Kubernetes/Docker is unavailable:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services import AgentCubeProvider\n\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=True)\n\n# This works without actual Kubernetes cluster\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n    image_url=\"test:latest\",\n    port=8080,\n)\n\n# Returns mock result\nprint(result)\n# {\n#     'name': 'test-agent',\n#     'namespace': 'default',\n#     'endpoint': 'http://test-agent.default.svc.cluster.local:8080',\n#     'env_vars': {}\n# }\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Services Architecture](/docs/architecture/services)\n- [Runtime Operations](/docs/architecture/runtime)\n- [CLI Reference](/docs/api/sdk-cli)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/ope