{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887957187,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2b0c23001FZwrD6G68CWnsD","messageID":"msg_d7b2aff43001HS3t6qv9qWGT0A","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ff0438a2483f450b8a979fd7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-runtime\ntitle: Runtime API\ndescription: Complete API reference for runtime operation classes\nsidebar_position: 4\n---\n\n# Runtime API\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube CLI uses runtime operation classes to handle the agent deployment lifecycle. These classes can also be imported and used programmatically.\n\n## PackRuntime\n\nPacks an agent workspace for deployment.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nPackRuntime(verbose: bool = False)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### pack\n\n```python\nruntime.pack(\n    workspace_path: str = \".\",\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None,\n    language: Optional[str] = None,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    port: Optional[int] = None,\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = None,\n    description: Optional[str] = None,\n    output: Optional[str] = None,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nPacks an agent workspace.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override agent name |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override entrypoint |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `output` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path |\n\n**Returns**:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"workspace_path\": \"/path/to/workspace\",\n    \"output_path\": \"/path/to/agentcube-pack\",\n    \"metadata_file\": \"/path/to/agentcube-pack/metadata.yaml\",\n    \"dockerfile_generated\": True,\n}\n```\n\n## BuildRuntime\n\nBuilds a Docker image from a packed workspace.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import BuildRuntime\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nBuildRuntime(verbose: bool = False)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### build\n\n```python\nruntime.build(\n    workspace_path: str,\n    proxy: Optional[str] = None,\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None,\n    output: Optional[str] = None,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nBuilds a Docker image.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | Required | Path to packed workspace |\n| `proxy` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL |\n| `cloud_provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name |\n| `output` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n\n**Returns**:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"image_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"image_tag\": \"v1.0.0\",\n    \"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n    \"version\": \"v1.0.0\",\n}\n```\n\n## PublishRuntime\n\nPublishes/deploys an agent to the target provider.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import PublishRuntime\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nPublishRuntime(\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n)\n```\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n| `provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider |\n\n### Methods\n\n#### publish\n\n```python\nruntime.publish(\n    workspace_path: str = \".\",\n    version: Optional[str] = None,\n    image_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    image_username: Optional[str] = None,\n    image_password: Optional[str] = None,\n    description: Optional[str] = None,\n    region: Optional[str] = None,\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None,\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    replicas: Optional[int] = None,\n    namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nPublishes an agent.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to workspace |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version |\n| `image_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL |\n| `image_username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Registry username |\n| `image_password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Registry password |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `cloud_provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name |\n| `provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider |\n| `node_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | NodePort (30000-32767) |\n| `replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas |\n| `namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n\n**Returns**:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n    \"endpoint\": \"http://my-agent.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n    \"status\": \"deployed\",\n}\n```\n\n### Providers\n\n| Provider | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `agentcube` | Deploy via AgentRuntime CRD |\n| `k8s` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes resources |\n\n## InvokeRuntime\n\nInvokes a published agent.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import InvokeRuntime\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nInvokeRuntime(\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### invoke\n\n```python\nruntime.invoke(\n    workspace_path: str = \".\",\n    payload: str = \"{}\",\n    header_list: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n    verbose: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nInvokes an agent.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to workspace |\n| `payload` | `str` | `\"{}\"` | JSON-formatted input |\n| `header_list` | `Optional[list[str]]` | `None` | Custom HTTP headers |\n| `provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n\n**Returns**:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"payload\": {\"message\": \"Hello!\"},\n    \"response\": {\"response\": \"Hello back!\", \"status\": \"success\"},\n}\n```\n\n## StatusRuntime\n\nChecks the status of a published agent.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n\n### Installation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import StatusRuntime\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nStatusRuntime(\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n)\n```\n\n### Methods\n\n#### get_status\n\n```python\nruntime.get_status(\n    workspace_path: str = \".\",\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\nGets agent status.\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workspace_path` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to workspace |\n| `provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider |\n\n**Returns**:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"agent_id\": \"agent-abc123\",\n    \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n    \"status\": \"Running\",\n    \"endpoint\": \"http://my-agent.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n    \"namespace\": \"agentcube\",\n}\n```\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Programmatic Deployment\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import (\n    PackRuntime,\n    BuildRuntime,\n    PublishRuntime,\n)\n\n# Pack workspace\npacker = PackRuntime(verbose=True)\npack_result = packer.pack(\n    workspace_path=\"./my-agent\",\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    language=\"python\",\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    port=8080\n)\nprint(f\"Packed: {pack_result['output_path']}\")\n\n# Build image\nbuilder = BuildRuntime(verbose=True)\nbuild_result = builder.build(\n    workspace_path=pack_result['output_path'],\n)\nprint(f\"Built: {build_result['image_name']}:{build_result['image_tag']}\")\n\n# Publish agent\npublisher = PublishRuntime(verbose=True, provider=\"agentcube\")\npublish_result = publisher.publish(\n    workspace_path=pack_result['output_path'],\n    version=build_result['version'],\n)\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {publish_result['endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n### Invoke and Check Status\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.runtime import InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime\n\n# Invoke agent\ninvoker = InvokeRuntime(verbose=True)\nresult = invoker.invoke(\n    workspace_path=\"./my-agent\",\n    payload='{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n)\nprint(result['response'])\n\n# Check status\nstatus = StatusRuntime(verbose=True)\nstatus_result = status.get_status(\n    workspace_path=\"./my-agent\",\n)\nprint(f\"Status: {status_result['status']}\")\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {status_result['endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n## Workflow Integration\n\nThese runtime classes are also used internally by the CLI commands:\n\n```python\n# Equivalent to: kubectl agentcube pack -f ./workspace\nfrom agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime\nruntime = PackRuntime(verbose=False)\nresult = runtime.pack(workspace_path=\"./workspace\")\n\n# Equivalent to: kubectl agentcube build -f ./workspace\nfrom agentcube.runtime import BuildRuntime\nruntime = BuildRuntime(verbose=False)\nresult = runtime.build(workspace_path=\"./agentcube-pack\")\n\n# Equivalent to: kubectl agentcube publish -f ./workspace\nfrom agentcube.runtime import PublishRuntime\nruntime = PublishRuntime(verbose=False)\nresult = runtime.publish(workspace_path=\"./workspace\")\n\n# Equivalent to: kubectl agentcube invoke -f ./workspace\nfrom agentcube.runtime import InvokeRuntime\nruntime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=False)\nresult = runtime.invoke(workspace_path=\"./workspace\")\n\n# Equivalent to: kubectl agentcube status -f ./workspace\nfrom agentcube.runtime import StatusRuntime\nruntime = StatusRuntime(verbose=False)\nresult = runtime.get_status(workspace_path=\"./workspace\")\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Runtime Operations](/docs/architecture/runtime)\n- [CLI Reference](/docs/api/sdk-cli)\n- [Services API](/docs/api/sdk-services)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] 