{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887990986,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2bc956001ezpuUWtyifdvJB","messageID":"msg_d7b2bbcfb001wudroGh3cYfZbw","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_66e1abd147ee437987eef507","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-exceptions\ntitle: Exceptions Reference\ndescription: Complete reference for AgentCube exception classes\nsidebar_position: 5\n---\n\n# Exceptions Reference\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube SDK defines a hierarchy of exception classes for different error conditions. All exceptions inherit from the base `AgentCubeError` class.\n\n## Exception Hierarchy\n\n```mermaid\nclassDiagram\n    class AgentCubeError {\n        <<abstract>>\n        +message: str\n    }\n    \n    class SessionError {\n        +session_id: Optional[str]\n    }\n    \n    class DataPlaneError {\n        +status_code: Optional[int]\n    }\n    \n    class CommandExecutionError {\n        +exit_code: Optional[int]\n        +stderr: Optional[str]\n        +command: Optional[str]\n    }\n    \n    AgentCubeError <|-- SessionError\n    AgentCubeError <|-- DataPlaneError\n    AgentCubeError <|-- CommandExecutionError\n```\n\n## Exception Classes\n\n### AgentCubeError\n\nBase exception class for all AgentCube errors.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import AgentCubeError\n\ntry:\n    # AgentCube operations\n    pass\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    print(f\"AgentCube error: {e}\")\n```\n\n### SessionError\n\nRaised when a session operation fails.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n#### Use Cases\n\n- Session bootstrap fails (network error, timeout)\n- Session not found in store\n- Invalid session ID\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import SessionError\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://invalid-url\")\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    # router_url not provided\n    print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\nexcept SessionError as e:\n    print(f\"Session error: {e}\")\n    print(f\"Session ID: {e.session_id}\")\n```\n\n### DataPlaneError\n\nRaised when a data plane operation fails.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n#### Use Cases\n\n- Invocation request fails (network error, timeout)\n- Agent returns error response\n- Invalid response format\n\n#### Properties\n\n| Property | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `message` | `str` | Error message |\n| `status_code` | `Optional[int]` | HTTP status code if available |\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import DataPlaneError\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n\ntry:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"test\"})\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\n    print(f\"Status code: {e.status_code}\")\n```\n\n### CommandExecutionError\n\nRaised when a command execution returns a non-zero exit code.\n\n**File**: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n\n#### Use Cases\n\n- Shell command fails\n- Code execution error\n- Script returns non-zero exit code\n\n#### Properties\n\n| Property | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `message` | `str` | Error message |\n| `exit_code` | `Optional[int]` | Command exit code |\n| `stderr` | `Optional[str]` | Standard error output |\n| `command` | `Optional[str]` | Command that was executed |\n\n#### Example\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n\ntry:\n    result = client.execute_command(\"exit 1\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    print(f\"Command failed: {e}\")\n    print(f\"Exit code: {e.exit_code}\")\n    print(f\"Stderr: {e.stderr}\")\n    print(f\"Command: {e.command}\")\n```\n\n## Error Handling Patterns\n\n### Basic Error Handling\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient\n\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Typed Error Handling\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import (\n    AgentCubeError,\n    SessionError,\n    DataPlaneError,\n    CommandExecutionError,\n)\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient\n\n# For AgentRuntimeClient\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\nexcept SessionError as e:\n    # Handle session-specific errors\n    print(f\"Session error: {e}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    # Handle data plane errors\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    # Handle any AgentCube error\n    print(f\"AgentCube error: {e}\")\n\n# For CodeInterpreterClient\ntry:\n    client = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    result = client.execute_command(\"ls\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    # Command execution failed\n    print(f\"Command failed with exit code {e.exit_code}\")\n    print(f\"Error output: {e.stderr}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    # Connection or protocol error\n    print(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    print(f\"AgentCube error: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import DataPlaneError\n\ndef invoke_with_fallback(client, payload):\n    try:\n        return client.invoke(payload)\n    except DataPlaneError as e:\n        # Return fallback response\n        return {\"error\": \"Agent unavailable\", \"details\": str(e)}\n```\n\n### Logging Errors\n\n```python\nimport logging\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import AgentCubeError\n\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.ERROR)\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"test\"})\nexcept AgentCubeError as e:\n    logger.error(f\"AgentCube operation failed: {e}\", exc_info=True)\n```\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Error Type | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| `SessionError` | Session creation or lookup failed |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Data plane communication failed |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Command returned non-zero exit code |\n\n## HTTP Status Mapping\n\n| HTTP Status | Exception |\n|-------------|-----------|\n| 400 | `DataPlaneError` |\n| 401 | `DataPlaneError` (Unauthorized) |\n| 404 | `SessionError` (Not Found) |\n| 429 | `DataPlaneError` (Rate Limited) |\n| 500 | `DataPlaneError` (Server Error) |\n| 502 | `DataPlaneError` (Bad Gateway) |\n| 503 | `DataPlaneError` (Service Unavailable) |\n| 504 | `DataPlaneError` (Gateway Timeout) |\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Always Close Clients\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\ntry:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n\n# Or use context manager\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\") as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"Hello\"})\n```\n\n### Check Exit Codes\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\ntry:\n    result = client.execute_command(\"my_script.sh\")\nexcept CommandExecutionError as e:\n    # Handle specific exit codes\n    if e.exit_code == 127:\n        print(\"Command not found\")\n    elif e.exit_code == 1:\n        print(\"General error\")\n    print(f\"Details: {e.stderr}\")\n```\n\n### Use Specific Exceptions\n\n```python\n# Bad: Catching all exceptions\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke(payload)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n\n# Good: Catching specific exceptions\ntry:\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(router_url=\"http://localhost:8081\")\n    response = client.invoke(payload)\nexcept SessionError as e:\n    print(f\"Session problem: {e}\")\nexcept DataPlaneError as e:\n    print(f\"Invocation problem: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Agent Runtime API](/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime)\n- [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter)\n- [Error Handling Guide](/docs/guides/error-handling)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [107:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [135:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [137:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [145:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable to \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":146,"character":61},"end":{"line":146,"character":68}},"message":"Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":152,"character":30},"end":{"line":152,"character":36}},"message":"\"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"","sever