{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888023507,"sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2c4d7e001jctBOKbZ2kINje","messageID":"msg_d7b2c4101001UTVQrUy2AxCpKr","sessionID":"ses_284db00daffeueA4MI8UK3vNOb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_48f6e5c139d34826ba888806","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\nid: sdk-cli\ntitle: CLI Reference\ndescription: Complete reference for kubectl-agentcube CLI commands\nsidebar_position: 6\n---\n\n# CLI Reference\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl agentcube`) provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of agent runtimes.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube\n```\n\nVerify installation:\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube --version\n```\n\n## Global Options\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `--verbose, -v` | Enable verbose output |\n| `--version` | Show version information |\n| `--help` | Show help message |\n\n## Commands\n\n### pack\n\nPacks an agent workspace for deployment.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `-f, --workspace PATH` | Path to agent workspace | `\".\"` |\n| `--agent-name TEXT` | Override agent name | Auto-detect |\n| `--language TEXT` | Programming language (python, java) | Auto-detect |\n| `--entrypoint TEXT` | Override entrypoint command | From metadata |\n| `--port INTEGER` | Port to expose | `8080` |\n| `--build-mode TEXT` | Build strategy (local, cloud) | `\"local\"` |\n| `--description TEXT` | Agent description | From metadata |\n| `--output PATH` | Output path for packaged workspace | `./agentcube-pack` |\n| `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging | False |\n| `--version` | Show version information | False |\n\n#### Example\n\n```bash\n# Pack current directory\nkubectl agentcube pack\n\n# Pack with custom agent name\nkubectl agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent\n\n# Pack with custom language and entrypoint\nkubectl agentcube pack --language python --entrypoint \"python main.py\"\n\n# Pack to custom output location\nkubectl agentcube pack --output /tmp/my-agent-packed\n```\n\n---\n\n### build\n\nBuilds a container image from a packed workspace.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `-f, --workspace PATH` | Path to the agent workspace directory | `\".\"` |\n| `-p, --proxy TEXT` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution | None |\n| `--cloud-provider TEXT` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) | None |\n| `--output PATH` | Output path for build artifacts | None |\n| `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging | False |\n\n#### Example\n\n```bash\n# Build from packed workspace\nkubectl agentcube build\n\n# Build with proxy\nkubectl agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n\n# Build and specify output\nkubectl agentcube build --output ./build-output\n```\n\n---\n\n### publish\n\nPublishes/deploys an agent to the target provider.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `-f, --workspace PATH` | Path to the agent workspace directory | `\".\"` |\n| `--version TEXT` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) | Auto |\n| `--image-url TEXT` | Image repository URL | Auto |\n| `--image-username TEXT` | Username for image repository | None |\n| `--image-password TEXT` | Password for image repository | None |\n| `--description TEXT` | Agent description | None |\n| `--region TEXT` | Deployment region | None |\n| `--cloud-provider TEXT` | Cloud provider name | None |\n| `--provider TEXT` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `--node-port INTEGER` | NodePort (30000-32767) | None |\n| `--replicas INTEGER` | Number of replicas | None |\n| `--namespace TEXT` | Deployment namespace | None |\n| `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging | False |\n\n#### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Publish to AgentCube\nkubectl agentcube publish\n\n# Publish to AgentCube with version\nkubectl agentcube publish --version v1.0.0\n\n# Publish to Kubernetes with NodePort\nkubectl agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080\n\n# Publish with custom image registry\nkubectl agentcube publish --image-url registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\n\n# Publish with authentication\nkubectl agentcube publish --image-username user --image-password pass\n\n# Publish with custom namespace\nkubectl agentcube publish --namespace my-namespace --replicas 3\n```\n\n---\n\n### invoke\n\nInvokes a published agent.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube invoke [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `-f, --workspace PATH` | Path to the agent workspace directory | `\".\"` |\n| `--payload TEXT` | JSON-formatted input passed to the agent | `\"{}\"` |\n| `--header TEXT` | Custom HTTP headers (key:value format) | None |\n| `--provider TEXT` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging | False |\n\n#### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Invoke with default payload\nkubectl agentcube invoke\n\n# Invoke with custom payload\nkubectl agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n\n# Invoke with complex payload\nkubectl agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Analyze\", \"data\": {\"type\": \"text\"}}'\n\n# Invoke with custom headers\nkubectl agentcube invoke --header \"X-Custom-Header:value\"\n\n# Invoke to K8s provider\nkubectl agentcube invoke --provider k8s\n```\n\n---\n\n### status\n\nChecks the status of a published agent.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube status [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n#### Options\n\n| Option | Description | Default |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `-f, --workspace PATH` | Path to the agent workspace directory | `\".\"` |\n| `--provider TEXT` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' | `\"agentcube\"` |\n| `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging | False |\n\n#### Example\n\n```bash\n# Check status\nkubectl agentcube status\n\n# Check status for K8s provider\nkubectl agentcube status --provider k8s\n```\n\n---\n\n### version\n\nShows version information.\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube version\n```\n\n#### Example\n\n```bash\n$ kubectl agentcube version\nAgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: 1.0.0\n```\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router service URL (used by SDK) |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL (used by SDK) |\n\n## Configuration Files\n\nThe CLI uses `metadata.yaml` in the workspace directory:\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: A helpful assistant\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\n```\n\n## Workflow Examples\n\n### Complete Deployment Workflow\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack the workspace\nkubectl agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python\n\n# 2. Build the Docker image\nkubectl agentcube build\n\n# 3. Publish the agent\nkubectl agentcube publish --version v1.0.0\n\n# 4. Invoke the agent\nkubectl agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello!\"}'\n\n# 5. Check status\nkubectl agentcube status\n```\n\n### K8s Deployment\n\n```bash\n# Pack and build\nkubectl agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent\nkubectl agentcube build\n\n# Publish to Kubernetes\nkubectl agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080 --replicas 3\n\n# Check status\nkubectl agentcube status --provider k8s\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe CLI returns exit codes:\n\n| Exit Code | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| 0 | Success |\n| 1 | Error (validation, network, etc.) |\n\nUse `--verbose` for detailed error information:\n\n```bash\nkubectl agentcube build --verbose\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\nThe CLI uses Rich for formatted output:\n\n```bash\n# Success output\n╭──────────────────────────────────────╮\n│         Pack Complete                │\n├──────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Agent Name:     my-agent             │\n│ Workspace:      ./workspace          │\n│ Output:         ./agentcube-pack     │\n│ Dockerfile:     Generated           │\n╰──────────────────────────────────────╯\n```\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Runtime Operations](/docs/architecture/runtime)\n- [Services API](/docs/api/sdk-services)\n- [Quick Start Guide](/docs/getting-started/quickstart)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assig